title: broiled scallops
directions: Combine mustard, honey, curry and lemon juice.
Brush onto scallops.
Broil under low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn, and brush scallops again.
Cook until lightly brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator 24 hours before serving.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joints; remove tips and discard.
Wash and pat dry on paper towel.
Combine remaining ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Arrange wings in single layer in marinade; cover and refrigerate for several hours, turning occasionally.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes, until tender.
Serve from chafing dish or fondue pot in sauce.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In large bowl, layer as follows:

title: tomato lasagne roll-ups
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Lay flat on foil to cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, heat oil.
Add onions; cook, stirring frequently, until tender and add tomatoes and tomato paste.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 5 minutes, stirring to break up tomatoes; set aside.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in Coca-Cola; chill for 1 hour.
Fold in other ingredients with juices.
Chill until firm.
Serve on lettuce beds.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
In the morning drain, rinse and bring 2 1/2 quarts water to boil with the beans and a ham hock. Reduce heat and simmer 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Add onion, tomato sauce or tomatoes, chili powder and garlic.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Makes about 8 to 10 servings.

title: porcupines
directions: Heat tomato juice, sugar, cloves and Worcestershire sauce in skillet while preparing meat.
Mix rest of ingredients together. With wet hands, form into balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Remove cloves from tomato sauce; put in the meatballs.
Cover tightly.
Simmer for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese dish
directions: Heat cheese with soup in pan.
Pour over mixed vegetables and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix flour, butter and salt like pie crust, but not too fine. Mix yeast, sugar and milk together.
Add egg yolks.
Add this to first mixture.
Don't stir too much; keep batter lumpy. Refrigerate overnight or for 3 to 4 hours.
Separate into 4 parts. Roll each part into circle the size of 9-inch pie plate.
Cut into 8 pieces as if you were cutting a pie.
Roll into crescent shaped horns.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.

title: jiffy hollandaise
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook and stir over low heat until heated through.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: wild rice dressing
directions: Remove the liver from the giblets, if desired. Place giblets and water in a saucepan. Cover and simmer for 2 hours or until tender.

title: russian tea
directions: Sift together all ingredients 3 times (for finer consistency, put in food processor).
Place 2 teaspoons of mixture (more or less to taste) in a cup.
Pour in hot water for a delicious hot drink.

title: ham and asparagus devine
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, line bottom with sliced ham. Place asparagus on top of ham.

title: jumbo cheese filled shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to directions; drain. Cool in a single layer on wax paper or aluminum foil to keep shells from sticking together. Combine cheeses, eggs, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper. Mix well. Fill each shell with about 1 1/2 tablespoons of cheese mixture. Spread a thin layer of sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Place shells in pan; cover with remaining sauce. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired. Cover with aluminum foil; bake at 350° for about 35 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Whip the whipping cream; blend in mayonnaise and cream cheese. Fold in fruit and juices.
Put in refrigerator tray and freeze. Serve on crisp lettuce.

title: applesauce cake(this recipe is over 100 years old)
directions: Cream sugar
and
shortening.
Add other ingredients in order given.
Blend well.
Bake
in
greased
tube pan in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Done when straw inserted comes out clean.

title: chili
directions: Boil beans until soft.
Add tomatoes.
Fry up hamburger and add to beans and tomatoes.
Add chili powder to your taste.
Some like it hot.
Add as much as your taste requires.
The more chili powder, the hotter it gets.
Use crock-pot or let simmer until ready to eat.
I put small onion in beans while cooking.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage and onion. Blend salad dressing, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Pour over vegetables and toss.

title: barbecue ribs
directions: Place ribs in small roaster and cover with sliced onions. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and let brown about 30 minutes.
Baste once in a while during baking.

title: turkey or shrimp gumbo
directions: Saute onion until tender in oil.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cooked rice, heat and serve.
Shrimp can be used instead of turkey.

title: soft ginger cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; add molasses.
Add vinegar and add dry ingredients.
Add soda and water.
Add extra flour for thicker cookies.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: strawberry soup slurp
directions: Let berries thaw a little bit.
Put them in a blender; set the speed of blender to puree or high speed.
Blend berries until they are liquid.
Pour liquid into a bowl; stir in honey and vanilla. Add yogurt and milk; stir slowly.
Chill the soup in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: quick corn and chili casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together corn, eggs, cornmeal, garlic and vegetable oil. Place half of the corn mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle on chilies and cheese.
Pour remaining half of corn mixture on top.
Bake 45 minutes or until mixture is firm and lightly golden. Serve immediately.

title: pasta chicken salad
directions: Coat breasts with oregano, lemon pepper, garlic and oil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover for last 15 minutes.
Boil the pasta.

title: chicken-spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and diced chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix everything well.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch Corning Ware dish.
Sprinkle with the following topping mix.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream lard and butter. Add sugar; blend until light. Add egg; continue to beat. Add vanilla and dry ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet; flatten with fork. Brush with cream, sprinkle with sugar, and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: best ever summer pasta
directions: Mix all the sauce ingredients and let set at room temperature for 1 hour or more.
Cook and drain pasta.
Serve hot in warmed bowls, topped with a ladleful of sauce and garnished with Parmesan. Serves 4 to 5.

title: bourbon balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1/4 cup confectioners sugar, stirring well. Form dough into about 48 small balls. (If balls tend to crumble, stir in a few extra drops of bourbon.) Roll each in confectioners sugar. Refrigerate in airtight container for about 1 week to mellow. Serves 24 (2 cookies per serving).

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat together egg and milk.
Combine with dry ingredients and form finger shaped patties.
Deep fry at 370° until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.

title: fresh broccoli-mandarin salad
directions: In top of double boiler, whisk together egg yolk, sugar, cornstarch and mustard.
Combine vinegar and water.
Slowly pour into egg mixture, whisking constantly.
Place over hot water and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and mayonnaise.
Chill.
Toss dressing with remaining ingredients and serve.

title: western casserole
directions: Brown
beef
in skillet.
Stir in remaining ingredients and bring
to
a
boil.
Turn mixture into a 2 quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in skillet; add flour, salt and pepper.
Cook for a minute.
Add milk gradually.
Cook, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Add cheese; stir well.
Cook macaroni; spoon half into butter 2-quart baking dish.
Add half the cheese sauce and repeat.
Bake in moderate 350° oven until mixture bubbles and is slightly browned on top.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Cut up the lemon after squeezing out all the juice into pieces.
Put into saucepan.
Mix together all of the ingredients. Let mixture simmer for a few minutes.
This sauce can be used on all kinds of meats: pork, chicken, beef, etc.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook 10 minutes.
(You can add hamburger, cooked and drained.)

title: potato puffs
directions: Beat eggs and mashed potatoes together.
Gradually add flour, baking powder and salt.
Drop from spoon into deep hot fat and fry until golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan.
Using electric mixer on low speed, mix first 5 ingredients until moistened.
Add eggs one at a time, beating at medium speed for 1 minute after each egg addition.
Pour batter into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Cool for 30 minutes before turning out of pan.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when completely cooled.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding mixes.
Add marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: dorothy's chicken
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Sprinkle flour, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, garlic powder and chopped onion.
Heat milk and butter.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: golden whipped potatoes
directions: Cut carrots into 1-inch chunks.
Quarter potatoes.
Combine carrots, potatoes and 2 cups water in a 3 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to boiling, covered.
Reduce heat; simmer for 40 minutes, or until vegetables are very tender.
Drain well.
Return vegetables to saucepan.
Beat with portable electric mixer (or mash with potato masher) until smooth, then heat mixture slowly, stirring, over low heat to dry out, about 5 minutes.
Add milk, 1 tablespoon butter, nutmeg, salt and pepper; beat until fluffy.
Pile lightly into serving dish.
Top with rest of butter.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: senator russell's sweet potatoes
directions: Remove skins from potatoes.
Thoroughly mix together potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla extract, and butter.
Pour into buttered casserole.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine sugars, soda, powder, flour and margarine.
Mix until crumbly (I use my hands).
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture for topping.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
To make sour milk, add 1 tablespoon of vinegar to your sweet milk.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cup reserved mixture.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna "lasagna"
directions: Cook noodles.
Put half in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add tuna, soup and milk.
Pour over noodles.
Top with cheese cut in strips.
Layer remaining noodles; top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until "bubbly."

title: honey cake
directions: Heat
oven
to
Mix together honey, brown sugar, oil and eggs in large bowl.
Add flour, baking soda and baking powder, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Stir in coffee and 1/3 cup raisins.
If
all
the raisins are mixed at one time, then tend to go to the bottom.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup raisins on top of
cake
before
it
goes
into
oven.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: smoked turkey breast
directions: Will also need a smoker pan.

title: pork chops al maria
directions: Brown chops in hot oil on both sides; transfer to a saucepan. Saute mushrooms and pepper in remaining oil; spread over chops, then saute onion.
Add tomatoes and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over chops; season with salt and pepper.
Cover tightly and simmer until tender, about 30 minutes.
Serve at once.
Serves six.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring just to a boil.
To serve, sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: favorite snack mix
directions: In a large bowl, combine the cereal, nuts and pretzels. In a small saucepan over low heat, melt butter. Add brown sugar; cook and stir until dissolved. Pour over cereal mixture; stir to coat. Place 1/3 on a greased 15 x 1-inch baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 minutes and bake for 6 minutes more. Spread on waxed paper to cool. Repeat with remaining mixture. Makes about 14 cups.

title: cheese grits
directions: Add egg to grits when done.
Add cheese and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and pour into baking dish and top with cheese.
Bake in pan of water at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy buttercream candy
directions: Cream butter in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and sweetened condensed milk.
Beat until blended.
Add powdered sugar, 2 cups at a time, blending well after each addition.
Knead until smooth.
Form into small balls and refrigerate until firm.
Melt chocolate and paraffin over hot water and with toothpick dip each candy into chocolate mixture until coated.
Put onto waxed paper.
Use leftover chocolate to drizzle on top of chocolate candy to cover hole left by toothpick.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: *Adding onions and bell pepper is optional.

title: wassail
directions: Combine juices in large kettle.
Add sugar and spices.
Heat until hot.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion (crisp-tender); drain.
Mix in mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish; sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Drizzle melted margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's clam sauce
directions: Saute minced garlic in olive oil until light brown (the more garlic the better!).
Drain clams.
Add juice only to sauteed garlic.
Save bottled juice.
Add salt, pepper and basil.
Heat for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Add clams.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add chopped parsley and tarragon (just a sprinkle).

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: *Pudding flavors: Butter pecan, butterscotch, milk chocolate, chocolate fudge, French vanilla or vanilla flavor.

title: pineapple squares
directions: Mix together.
Place the mixture in a buttered 9 x 9-inch pan. Add the cooled filling mixture.
Make a meringue with 2 egg whites.
Spread on top and bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice sweet potatoes lengthwise 1/4-inch thick. Place in pan with small amount of oil.
Fry slow until tender, when pierced with a fork.
Turn over and salt lightly.
Goes good with turnip greens or collards.

title: date krispies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler and cook for 7 minutes, stirring often.
Add rest of ingredients; roll into small balls, then in coconut.
Makes 70 cookies.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop from tip of a spoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add at once the bananas, strawberries and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into pan and allow to get firm.
Cover with sour cream.
Pour remaining strawberry mixture on top of sour cream.
Return to refrigerator.
Chill until firm.

title: scotch trifle
directions: Make jello according to directions.
Refrigerate until mixture is very syrupy.
Cook pudding according to directions and let cool.
Place 1/2 of the cake pieces in a large bowl.
Spread with jam and sprinkle with liquor.
Pour on 1/2 of jello and 1/2 of pudding.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate to mellow flavor.
Before serving, whip the cream with sugar until thick.
Cover top of trifle with whipped cream.

title: blackeyed peas & ham
directions: In hot margarine & oil saute: chopped onion, celery, thyme leaves, bay leaves, Stirring 5 minutes.
Add salt & black pepper to taste, 1/4 c. brown sugar.

title: mother's corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter baking pan real well.
Mix, by hand, all ingredients well except chunks of butter.
Pour into prepared pan and dot top with small chunks of butter.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir well and reduce oven to 325°.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour more.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple well and put juice in a large bowl.
Heat juice 1 to 2 minutes on high (juice should be hot but not boiling).
Add and dissolve jello.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk and pineapple.
Refrigerate until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in dessert topping and nuts.
Pour into a large Pyrex dish or several small molds.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Pour Prego in large skillet; mix in browned hamburger.
Let simmer on low heat with spices for 30 minutes.
Mix in Parmesan. Cut heat off.
Mix in cooked spaghetti.
Pour into a square Pyrex dish; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: delightful punch
directions: Pour ginger ale and punch in a large punch bowl.
Spoon sherbet into mixture.

title: potato fritters
directions: Scrub, peel and grate the potatoes.
Mix with other ingredients.
Heat a little oil or fat in a pan and fry spoonfuls of the mixture until brown on both sides.
Makes 4 helpings.

title: cheryl's chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in water with lemon pepper, onion, garlic salt and salt.
Remove chicken when tender.
Add rice and simmer until tender.
Take chicken off bone and break in pieces.
Put in rice with cream of celery soup.
Add additional water if too thick. Simmer 5 minutes after adding soup.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream
milk, sugar and eggs.
Beat.
Add crackers, nuts and coconut.
Bake in three 9-inch pans at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jellied old-fashioned cole slaw
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water.
Add cold water and chill until syrupy.
Fold in remaining ingredients except cabbage. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cabbage.
Chill until firm.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pare eggplant and dice.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet.
Add green pepper and onion. Cook on low for a few minutes.
Add tomatoes, eggplant, salt and black pepper.
Cook 10 minutes.
Place in shallow greased dish. Melt 2 tablespoons butter; stir in bread crumbs and sprinkle over eggplant.
Bake until crumbs are brown, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: luscious grape pie
directions: Place grapes in uncooked pie crust.
Mix sugar, flour and egg well; spread over the grapes.
Add the top crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake approximately 25 minutes longer.

title: grandmother's chili sauce
directions: Briefly boil tomatoes to loosen skins.
Peel and allow to cool.
In large saucepan, combine vinegar, sugar, salt, cinnamon, pepper and cloves.
Bring to slow boil, stirring often.
Add tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Simmer at a low boil until mixture thickens.
Pour into sterilized pint canning jars.
Adjust lids and process for 15 minutes in water bath.
Thickening may take 2 hours.

title: sunshine loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Blend cream cheese in a bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Mix in pears and pineapple.
Add cake mix, flour and candied lemon peel and mix just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn into pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: angel delight congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O; let cool.
Cream cottage cheese with salad dressing.
Add pineapple and nuts to the cheese mixture.
Whip the cream.
Add sugar (or whip Carnation and add little lemon juice to kill canned flavor).
Fold in cream.
Ready to mold.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, corn syrup, sugar, chocolate, margarine and vanilla together.
Put pecan pieces into an unbaked pie crust.
Pour mixture over pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
To test, a knife should be inserted into the pie and it should come out clean.

title: crabmeat dip(appetizer)
directions: Mix.
Cook in pie tin at 325° about 25 minutes, until brown. Will brown sooner if sprinkled with a little bit of cheese.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Slice strawberries and soak in 1/2 cup sugar overnight. Prepare the white or yellow cake mix according to directions.
Bake in two layer pans.
Let cool.
In a medium bowl, add whipping cream, 1 cup sugar and lemon juice.
Mix. Place strawberries on first cake layer and spread cream over strawberries.
Repeat with second layer and cover cake with remaining cream.
Place strawberries on top and enjoy.

title: corn bread sticks
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk and melted shortening.
Add this to corn meal. Bake in hot, greased pan in the shape of bread sticks or ears of corn.
Put in hot oven (450°).
Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Makes about 12 sticks.

title: pepper steak
directions: Slice steak across the grain and marinate in oyster sauce, water, cornstarch, baking soda and 1 tablespoon of oil for 15 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine and let stand until solid.
Refrigerate.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain well.
Combine butter, soup and cheese in a microwave dish.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, checking and stirring after each minute.
Continue until melted.
Add broccoli and milk.
Heat on High for 3 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Arrange rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top.
Mix soup and water together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: eclair ring
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Drain all canned fruit and combine in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix gently.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 12 servings.

title: spanish meal
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Drain.
Add kidney beans, taco seasoning, mushrooms, taco sauce, jalapeno peppers and rice. Simmer.
Pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over the mixture and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange peel bread
directions: Combine molasses, sugar and egg.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Dissolve baking soda in coffee.
Add flour mixture and coffee mixture alternately to the molasses mixture.
Fold in orange peel.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients, except walnuts. Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake 40 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german spinach
directions: Boil spinach till tender. Saute onion in small amount of butter/margarine. Drain spinach and chop into pieces. Add chopped spinach into onion and simmer for a few minutes.
Add small amount of milk depending on amount of spinach.
Add 1 beaten egg, sprinkle Tbsp. flour into spinach and crumbled bacon. Serve warm. From German Pioneers/San Antonio.

title: cauliflower & broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces and place in a large mixing bowl. Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together. Pour over broccoli and cauliflower. Add 3 Tbsp. bacon bits. Let set at least 1 hour before serving.

title: one minute orange salad
directions: Break up 1 head lettuce in a deep bowl.
Next items are put on in layers:
Mushrooms, chives, parsley, chopped water chestnuts and olives (optional).
Cover with small jar of Hellmann's mayonnaise. Seal bowl with cellophane or plastic wrap or keep in Tupperware bowl with lid.
Set overnight in refrigerator.
Stir when ready to serve and add salt and pepper.
(Great as leftovers.)

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Cut cream cheese with fork and put in jello with ice cubes.
When it starts getting cold, take out ice and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and set in refrigerator to chill, then serve.

title: fruit punch
directions: Heat first 5 ingredients until dissolved.
Put the bananas in blender with small amount of pineapple juice; blend.
Combine all other ingredients. Put in freezer. Take out of the freezer 3 1/2 hours before serving. When ready to serve, add 5 (28 ounce) bottles ginger ale.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans into a glass bowl.
Add Worcestershire sauce and bacon bits.
Spread brown sugar on top of beans; then spread ketchup on top of brown sugar.
You can microwave or put in oven until brown sugar has dissolved.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Stir Jell-O, cornstarch, hot water and sugar together and cook over low heat until thickened.
Cool.
Bake a pie shell according to directions.
Cool.
Wash strawberries and cut off stems.
Drain. Put in pie shell.
Pour cooled filling over berries.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in a buttered casserole dish. Layer chicken pieces next.
Combine soup, mayo and lemon juice; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese on next.
Spread crumbs on next.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bean and rice soup
directions: Cook and stir bacon in large saucepan on medium heat until browned.
Add onion and celery; cook and stir until tender.
Add water, beans, tomato sauce, garlic powder, salt and pepper; cover. Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Makes 8 cups or 8 servings.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Lay rolls in pan (leaving room for them to raise).
Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Spread evenly over rolls.
Gently pour on melted butter.
Set in cold oven overnight.
When ready to bake, turn oven to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Do not preheat oven!

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer peas, soup, peas and cheese in two layers (in that order).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: party sandwich filling
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use as fillings between lightly buttered slices of sandwich bread.
Trim crusts.
Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: chili dip
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add ketchup, cumin, chili powder and salt.
Mash kidney beans with fork; add to meat mixture.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; set aside for 2 1/2 hours (covered).
Reheat in chafing dish.
To serve, sprinkle grated cheese, more chopped onion and chopped olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Replenish cheese and onion on top, as needed.

title: pimento cheese dip
directions: Beat together with mixture until smooth.
Use as vegetable dip or on crackers.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spread chicken pieces in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add eggs and Veg-All.
Mix broth and soup to pour over chicken mixture. Combine margarine, flour and milk to pour over top for the crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and powdered sugar together.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together.
Dip peanut butter balls in melted chocolate and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Let set until cool and store.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: One pound of chopped shrimp may be substituted for crabmeat.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Cut fruit into bite size pieces.
Mix with cocktail and marshmallows.
Add cool whip.
Stir well.

title: calico beans
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients, blending well.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with strips of bacon.
Sprinkle with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: custardy cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into well-greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until top is golden brown, but interior is still custardy.

title: melt in your mouth chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix soup and broth together in saucepot and bring to a boil.
Pour over chicken.
Make batter from remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and broth.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 425° oven.

title: heavenly mix
directions: Melt almond bark according to package direction exactly. Mix golden grahams and pretzels in the almonds bark, coating them evenly as possible, spread over wax paper. WORK QUICKLY!!! Let cool. Break apart into small chunks and put into air tight container.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken breasts between 2 sheets of wax paper to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet.
Place 1 slice ham and 1 slice cheese on each breast.
Roll up, beginning with long side. Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip by melba
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refill 16-ounce sour cream container with mayonnaise for easy measuring.
Be sure to drain or squeeze the water out of thawed spinach; a little extra chopping can be helpful for ease of serving.
Best if refrigerated overnight to allow dried vegetable soup mix to hydrate.

title: butterscotch sticks
directions: Melt butter and let cool.
Add brown sugar, stirring well, then add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour, salt and baking powder sifted together.
Add vanilla and nuts. Put in well greased pan.
Cook for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cut while warm into squares.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes approximately 50 squares.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In ungreased square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inches, stir together flour, granulated sugar, 2 tablespoons cocoa, the baking powder and salt.
Mix in milk, oil and vanilla with fork until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes; spoon into dessert dishes or cut into squares.
Invert each square onto dessert plate.
Top with ice cream and spoon sauce over each serving.

title: pineapple crunch
directions: Mix first five ingredients together.
Add crushed Ritz crackers on top.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
Add softened butter and blend well.
Stir in eggs, chips, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Pie will wiggle when done and set as it cools.

title: inflation cookies
directions: Combine ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls and press top of cookie
with
fork.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes. Time may vary according to ovens.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion with margarine.
Add cheeses.
Add cans of soup; add broccoli.
Heat until hot.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in a saucepan; set sugar mixture aside.
Combine egg yolks, water and lemon juice; stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and lemon rind. Spoon into pastry shell.
Spread meringue to edges of pie shell to seal it.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: In casserole, spread onion over chops.
Spread undiluted soup over top.
Cover and cook at 350° for about 45 minutes or until chops are done.
Serve over rice.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O according to package directions. Chill until it sets a little. Take out of refrigerator and add bananas, strawberries and pineapple to the Jell-O. Using a long pan (9 x 13-inch), pour half of the Jell-O mixture in pan.
Put the pan back into the refrigerator and chill until set.

Leave the other half of the Jell-O out. When the Jell-O is set, take out of refrigerator and spread a thin layer of sour cream. Add the remaining Jell-O and return to the refrigerator and chill until set.

title: dallas dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.
Makes 2 cups. Serve with chips.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake by box directions.
While cake is cooling, drain pineapple.
Punch holes in layer with toothpick.
Pour juice over layer.
Mix remaining items with pineapple and spread on layer. Do next two layers the same way.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: dump pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add fruit.
Mix flour, sugar and milk together.
Pour over fruit and margarine.
Do not stir.
Crust will cover pie.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: In a large saucepan, steam asparagus until tender;
drain and place on a serving platter.
In a small jar with a lid, shake together oil, lemon juice, mustard, pepper, and salt.
When ready to serve (warm or at room temperature), pour vinaigrette evenly over asparagus;
sprinkle with bread crumbs and garnish with cherry tomato halves.

title: squash cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil; add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add squash and nuts.
Mix. Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Watch closely after 45 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash beans well (use juice).
Beat eggs; add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300°.
Makes 3 pies.
(Freezes well.)

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Cream remaining sugar and shortening.
Pour boiling water over mixture. Add cold water, egg and yeast mixture.
Stir in flour and salt; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.
Place the portions of dough to be used on floured board and shape as desired or roll.
Dip rolls in melted butter and place in pan.
Let rise at room temperature until double in size.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 12 minutes.

title: russian tea balls
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add other ingredients. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 400° until light brown.
Cool 2 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: macaroni buffet skillet
directions: Dice green pepper, onion and garlic.
Saute with ground beef in olive oil.
Add uncooked macaroni.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving small amount of olives for garnishing top.
Stir in cheese sauce.
Cover tightly.
Cook on high heat until steaming freely, then turn to lowest heat for 25 to 30 minutes or until all ingredients are cooked to desired tenderness.
Stir occasionally. Serve in skillet.

title: turkey gumbo
directions: In a heavy pot, heat oil.
Add flour and stir constantly until the roux is brown, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Add the celery, onions, green pepper, garlic, okra and tomatoes.
Saute, stirring occasionally for about 15 minutes.
Add cold water all at once with salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco.
Bring to a rapid boil.
Add turkey carcass.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 1/2 hour or longer until stock is rich.
Taste for seasoning.
Add turkey cubes, parsley and green onions.
Cook for 10 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: dorthea's west haven date cake
directions: Pour hot water over chopped dates.
Add baking soda to mixture and set aside to cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix date mixture with creamed sugar, shortening and salt.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and cocoa.
Blend well.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, lightly greased.
Sprinkle batter with 1/2 cup Hershey's mini chocolate chips and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 325° if glass pan or 350° for tin pan.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.
Serves 15.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/3 of noodles to place on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nanny's lasagna
directions: Brown the ground beef and add tomato sauce, sour cream and sugar gradually.
Add the other spices.
When your sauce is complete, layer on your prepared noodles and the cheeses between layers and a final layer of cheese on the top.
Bake at 350°.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Brush mushroom caps with butter.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Fill caps.
Place on broiler pan, filled side up. Broil 6 inches from heat about 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and mushrooms are heated through.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, covered, then 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour in buttered casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Pinch off dough and press flat on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: daddy's no-bake fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pack in baking pan.
Use a little of the cherry juice if you think cake is too dry.
Wrap in tinfoil and refrigerate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Boil sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear. Remove from heat, add food coloring and dry jello.
Let cool. Line pie crust with berries.
Don't sweeten or use juice. When filling is cooled, pour over berries and chill.
May serve with whipped cream.

title: stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Stir in hamburger, garlic, flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Saute 5 minutes.
Add soup; simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Serve over buttered noodles.

title: chocolate waffle iron cookies
directions: Melt chocolate with margarine or butter in saucepan over low heat; stirring constantly.
Beat eggs; add sugar, vanilla and flour.
Blend well and add to chocolate margarine mixture.
Heat iron to medium setting.
Drop batter by teaspoon onto waffle iron, making 4 to each square.
Bake 1/2 to 1 minute.
Place on racks to cool.
When cool, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: done buttered biscuits
directions: Mix together first 2 ingredients; add Bisquick.
Mix well and drop into small muffin tins.
(Can use large ones.)
Spray pans with Pam; bake for 12 minutes at 400°.
If large tins, bake for 15 minutes.

title: gold coin carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix rest of the ingredients well and pour over the carrots.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before using.
Keeps well for 2 weeks.

title: baked brisket
directions: Put brisket in roasting pan, fat side up.
Add other ingredients.
Add water to 1 inch.
Bake, covered, 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
Add potatoes and carrots in last hour.

title: skillet beef special
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and drain fat.
Add the next 4 ingredients; stir and simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Boil noodles and drain.
Add to beef mixture and toss.
Serve with a salad and French bread.
Serves 6.

title: monkey bread(coffee cake)
directions: Cut frozen dough rolls in half (about 1-inch pieces).
Melt butter and toss pieces in butter to coat.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon-sugar and toss with raisins, apples and nuts.
Place in a large greased bundt pan and cover pan with a towel.
Let rise overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees until golden brown.
Make a glaze with powdered sugar and milk and drizzle over bread.
(Raisins, apples, and pecans may be omitted.)

title: amy's garlic egg chicken
directions: In a glass dish, beat egg yolk with garlic.
Place chicken in egg mixture, and turn to coat.
Cover dish and refrigerate for at least 4 hours, or overnight if possible.
Preheat oven to 400°. Melt butter and pour into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix together the bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Dip marinated chicken in crumb mixture. Place coated chicken in baking dish and pour remaining egg mixture over.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 to 20 minutes on each side, or until chicken is no longer pink and juices run clear.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Combine all filling ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in filling 2 inches from crust comes out clean.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans, 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch or rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package except substitute pineapple and juice for the water.
Stir shredded coconut and rum flavoring into batter.
Pour batter into pans and bake as directed.
Cool layers 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool completely.

title: mile high strawberry pie
directions: Place defrosted berries, sugar, egg whites, lemon juice and salt in large mixing bowl of electric beater.
Beat at medium speed for 15 minutes or until stiff and mixture holds shape.
Whip cream and vanilla.
Add to strawberry mixture.
Pile lightly in shell.
Freeze overnight.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Mix thoroughly with 1 can of milk until smooth and thick. Enough for 3 cakes.

title: carolyn's hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate chips in evaporated milk over medium heat, stirring to prevent sticking to the bottom of the pot.
Add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add vanilla extract.
Beat until satiny.
Cool and refrigerate.
This fudge sauce may be prepared in a microwave oven.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Place in water and bring to a boil.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Heat in casserole dish or crock-pot until hot and rice is done, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: Place chopped chicken in a 9-inch greased casserole.
Cover with sliced eggs.
Combine flour and oleo in saucepan.
Add cream of chicken soup.
Heat and pour over eggs.
Sprinkle with cheese, split biscuits and place over top to cover casserole.
Bake at 350°
about 15 minutes or until biscuits are brown.
Makes 6 or 8 servings.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Boil haddock in water with vinegar and salt.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes if fish is frozen, less time if fresh.
Drain fish; place under broiler for a few minutes to dry out.
Serve with melted butter.
Tastes like lobster.

title: for fudge lovers
directions: Heat sugar, butter and evaporated milk to full rolling boil in 3-quart heavy saucepan on medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil on medium heat until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching, about 4 minutes. Remove from heat.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach completely. Squeeze out all excess water. Mix vegetable soup, sour cream and mayonnaise together. Mix all ingredients very well together. Prepare ahead of time so that mixture is refrigerated for at least 2 to 3 hours. Serve with pumpernickel bread, crackers or chips. Keep refrigerated.

title: spinach salad
directions: Add garlic to dressing.
Refrigerate.
Chop hard-boiled eggs, crumble cooked bacon and sprinkle over spinach.
Remove garlic from dressing and pour over spinach. Toss well. Serve at once. Also good with crabmeat added.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 325° and grease pans.
In a large bowl, combine pumpkin, sugar, butter, water and eggs.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Mix together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to first mixture and beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Stir in dates or raisins and nuts.
Pour in pans (2 loaf size) and bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon oatmeal pancakes
directions: Heat griddle or pan.
Beat all ingredients, except apples, in a medium bowl with a hand beater until smooth.
Stir in apples. Pour about 1/4 cup of batter into hot griddle.
Cook until puffy. Turn and cook other side until golden brown.

title: beef wellington
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle beef with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Place on rack in shallow pan.
Bake 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: funnel cake
directions: Pour oil into a deep fryer or a heavy deep pan until it's about 2 inches deep.
Get oil very hot, but not until it smokes. Pour mixed batter through a funnel into hot oil in a circular motion, then in a crisscross until cake is size of a large doughnut.
They cook quick!
When lightly brown, remove and drain on a paper towel.
While hot, dredge in powdered sugar or sprinkle on top.

title: love's soup
directions: Layer ingredients in glass jar.
Give away "cause a little love goes a long way."

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok.
Add onion; stir-fry until onion is limp. Add rice; continue to stir-fry until rice is thoroughly heated. Add soy sauce; mix well.
Add beaten eggs; stir until blended. Add peas; stir-fry until thoroughly heated.

title: tang fruit salad
directions: Combine all fruit.
Add Tang and pudding and mix well.

title: cheesy corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper until onion is transparent.
Stir in flour until smooth and then add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat; add cheese, salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir together, then add beaten eggs.
Pour into greased 7 x 10-inch Pyrex casserole.
Top with bread crumbs which have been tossed with 2 teaspoons of melted margarine.
Set in shallow pan of hot water.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Cream together butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to butter mixture.

title: angie's pork chops
directions: Preheat oven
to 350°.	Slice onion and potatoes.
Just cover the bottom	of
large
2-quart baking dish with cream of mushroom soup.
Next,
put
a
layer
of
potatoes
along
the bottom. Follow with a layer of onions.
Next comes a layer of pork chops. Cover this with cream of mushroom soup and repeat until ingredients are
gone.
The
last
layer
should also be cream of mushroom
soup.
Cover
and
bake
for 2 1/2 hours or until pork falls off of bone.

title: "can't goof homemade bread"
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add 2 cups of flour and remaining ingredients.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Add remaining flour; stir with a spoon.
Cover; allow to rise (double in size), about 30 minutes.
Punch down 25 strokes.
Pour in greased loaf pan; let rise to the top of pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°, until golden brown.
Brush with oleo.

title: yum-a-setta(a country family favorite)
directions: Brown hamburger with salt, pepper, brown sugar and onion.
Add tomato soup.
Cook egg noodles; drain.
Add cream of chicken soup. Layer hamburger mixture and noodle mixture in casserole dish wit process cheese between layers.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chocolate amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of a 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Put raisins in a bowl with boiling water.
When raisins are plump, then strain.
Add honey, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Toss in shredded carrots.

title: loaf dessert(salad)
directions: Cut everything quite fine, then mix together.
Form into loaf and roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Make the day before serving. Wrap in foil and refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients together; stir dry ingredients together, then mix into zucchini mixture.
Stir until moist. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eaton's waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into waffle iron and cook until done.
Serve with fresh strawberries, blueberries or peaches and maple syrup.
The mix can be made ahead of time. Serves 4.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add ketchup and brown sugar. Cook a few minutes.
Then add all of the beans.
Bake for 1 hour until it gets a little thick at 350°.
Put in a casserole dish.

title: diet strawberry milkshake
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender. Serves 1.

title: tamale recipe
directions: Simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in covered pot. Tamales and sauce may be frozen after cooking for future use.

title: shrimp mosca
directions: Cook sauce slowly for 10 to 15 minutes; do not boil.
Allow to cool slightly and add shrimp (50 to 60 medium).
Stir shrimp around in mixture.
Put in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours or overnight. Cook 18 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven, stirring several times. Serve with French bread and potato salad (use bread to dip in sauce).

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in 9 x 9-inch dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. May be made the night before and kept in refrigerator before baking and serving. Makes a complete breakfast.

title: fudgy cherry dessert
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine brownie mix, cherries and egg. Beat with spoon about 50 strokes or just until moistened.
Fold in chips.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake for 28 to 30 minutes or until dry on top.
Cool.
Cut into squares and top with ice cream.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in one egg yolk at a time.
Add bananas.
Add sifted flour, soda and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Add chopped nuts.

title: dilly garden rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Transfer to a large bowl; cover and chill.
Combine yogurt, sugar, salt and dill weed.
Stir into rice.
Stir in zucchini and onions.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Just before serving, stir in tomatoes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch tube pan (not fluted), or a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round cake pans.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt.
Add oil and beat at medium speed with electric mixer or for 2 minutes with wooden spoon until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add carrots, nuts, coconut and raisins. Continue beating until all mixed.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake for 1 hour 15 minutes or until tester comes out clean. Remove pan from oven and place on a wire rack to cool for 5 minutes.
Run a knife between edge of cake pan to loosen.
Turn out on rack to cool completely.
Will keep in refrigerator for a week or more wrapped tightly or covered in foil and up to 3 months in freezer.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper; stir often.
Add soups and water.
Cook spaghetti uncovered 8 minutes; add salt and drain well.
Combine spaghetti with the meat mixture and 1 cup of the cheese.
Mix well.
Put in a casserole (at least 3 quart) and top with 2 cups cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grate 1 teaspoon of the yellow zest and squeeze 1/4 cup juice from the lemons.
Separate the eggs.
With an electric mixer, set at medium speed, beat the yolks with the lemon zest, juice, sugar and salt until light yellow in color.
Beat in the milk.
Gradually add the flour, beating until smooth.

title: dill pickles
directions: Combine vinegar, water and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Wash cucumbers.
Pack jars; add dill and garlic.

title: holishka
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Combine bacon, noodles, cheese, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Soak raisins in water.
Beat eggs; stir in pumpkin, sugar, cloves, cinnamon and salt.
Add oil and mix well.
Stir together the flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add this to the pumpkin mixture.
Drain raisins and add to mixture.
Stir well.

title: buckeyes (peanut butter balls)
directions: Mix peanut butter, margarine, sugar and vanilla together. Form into 1-inch balls about the size of marbles. Chill. Melt chocolate coating in microwave. Dip balls into chocolate and place on waxed paper to harden. Store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, beaten egg and salt in a mixing bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat balls and bake at 325° until done.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Blend butter and flour in saucepan until smooth.
Gradually add milk and half and half stirring constantly.
Dissolve vegetable broth in small amount of hot water.
Add with remaining ingredients, except broccoli, to creamed mixture.
Cook until smooth, stirring constantly.
Stir in broccoli; heat thoroughly. Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados in blender until smooth.
Blend in sour cream and lemon juice, then add all other ingredients.
Blend well with spoon.
Serve with tacos or tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: honeymoon bars
directions: Mix first 3 items.
Spread in a 9 x 9-inch ungreased pan. Bake 10 minutes in 360° oven.

title: ground beef-noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck. Saute onions and garlic. Add to ground chuck mixture. Cook noodles according to package directions. Combine sour cream and cream cheese. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer noodles, ground chuck mixture and cream cheese-sour cream mixture. Sprinkle grated cheese on top. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until grated cheese is melted and dish is heated through.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Put all ingredients in covered casserole or bean pot.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: slice o' lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt. Blend in butter or oleo.
Add beaten eggs, reserving 1 teaspoon egg white. Blend until smooth. Add sliced lemon, rind and sugar mixture.
Stir in water. Blend well. Turn into a pastry-lined pan.

Top with second crust which has been slit to allow escape of steam. Seal and flute edges. Brush with reserved egg white and sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: ribbon meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except cheese.
Place half of mixture in 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Cover with remaining meat mixture.

title: pecan-fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, 2 cups flour and 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Add lemon extract; mix thoroughly.
Mix nuts and fruit in 2 cups flour.
Then add to preceeding mixture. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Cover with a cloth.
Let stand overnight at room temperature.
Pour into a greased Bundt cake pan.
(Make sure it is greased really heavy! I use oleo or spray really heavy with Pam.)
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Let cool all day (at least 12 hours) before removing from pan.
Check cake after cooking 2 hours to see if inside is cooked.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Melt margarine.
Add sugar, slightly beaten egg, yeast and flour.
Mix well.
Bake in greased muffin tin 20 minutes at 400°.
Will keep refrigerated a week.

title: german chocolate cake icing
directions: Cook milk, yolks, flour and oleo until thick.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Icing for box of German chocolate cake mix.

title: mexican chili roll
directions: Melt cheese until soft.
Mix all ingredients except chili powder.
Divide into 5 long rolls.
Roll in chili powder until covered.
Wrap each roll in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight. Serve with crisp crackers.
Will keep in refrigerator for several weeks.
This is a Tex Mex dish.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Grease two 9-inch round layer cake pans.
Line with wax paper, extending up sides of pans; grease wax paper.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for cake-like brownies; pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Cool. In large bowl, mix condensed milk and water; beat in pudding mix.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Place 1 brownie layer on serving plate.
Top with half each the pudding mixture and strawberries.
Repeat with other layer.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix ingredients in order:
sugar, flour, chocolate, water, vanilla, milk and butter.
Stir constantly until thick on medium setting.
Serve over homemade biscuits.

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix together then beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 X 12
cake pan and bake according to directions on box.
Cool Well.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and drain well.
Add drained can of red or kidney beans.
Tear lettuce.
Mince onions.
(Note:
Use a cutting board.)
Chop tomatoes, grate cheese.
Crush bag of corn chips. Toss all together and use favorite dressing or taco sauce.

title: no fuss caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn and peanuts in large brown grocery bag.
Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in 2-quart glass bowl or casserole. Microwave High for 4 minutes, stirring after each minute until mixture boils.
Microwave High 2 more minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Pour syrup over corn and nuts in bag.
Close bag; shake well.
Microwave High 1 1/2 minutes.
Close and shake bag well. Microwave High 1 1/2 minutes more.
Shake bag well.
Pour corn onto cookie sheet.
Stir with hands as it cools to separate kernels.
Be very careful you do not burn hands separating the corn.

title: sweet potato crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place in 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 15 minutes.
Take out of oven and add topping.

title: cajun sausage over rice
directions: Saute sausage, onions and bell pepper and add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook all day.
Serve over rice or spaghetti.

title: kids' quick snack
directions: Melt peanut butter and honey or syrup on stove top, then put corn flakes in quickly and put in buttered cookie sheet.
Cool, cut and eat.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown ground beef. Shape biscuits into greased muffin tins. Drain meat.
Add seasoning and tomato paste.
Stir together well. Spoon into biscuits and sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all and put in casserole.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Set oven at 375°.
Blend graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of an 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 8 minutes and cool.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup sugar; stir in pineapple with juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring briskly, until thickened and clear.
Cool; stir in lemon juice.
Spread pineapple mixture evenly over bottom of crumb crust.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise, lime juice, salt and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Top with whipped cream and serve.

title: peanut butter crescents
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: amish cookies
directions: Cream sugars, butter or margarine and oil until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Make into balls and press down with glass that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until they start to brown around edges.

title: date roll(very good)
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball in water.
Put in the dates and beat for about 3 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add the pecans and beat until it is beginning to get firm. Take it from the pan and roll it in a damp towel to shape it into a roll. When it is cold and firm, slice it into pieces, 1/2-inch thick.

title: enchiladas
directions: Gravy:
In a skillet, mix water, all spices, chili powder, salt and 2 to 3 tablespoons flour.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Cream the butter and brown sugar.
Add flour and nuts; mix. Set aside 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Press in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken duck(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Mix last 3 ingredients.
Pour over chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Serve with sauce over rice.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add oil and beat until creamy. Sift flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.

title: bourbon steak marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients; add steaks and marinate for minimum of 4 hours, overnight is great, turning once.
Grill.

title: tuna ball
directions: Mix together the tuna and cream cheese with onion soup mix. Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with stuffed olives. Refrigerate.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: In large bowl, beat sugar, vanilla, butter and milk until smooth.
Add more milk, if needed.
Stir in food coloring.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Spread into well-greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler and spread over mixture in pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Yields 24 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix together and put in freezer.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in top of a double boiler.
Mix in whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water, stirring constantly, until thick. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff and mixture will form stiff peaks.
Bake in oven at 425° for 5 minutes or until browned.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: In plastic bag mix flour, Parmesan cheese, salt, sage and pepper.
Shake chicken in bag and then place in baking dish. Cover with cream of chicken soup mixed with 1/2 can water.
Bake uncovered 1 hour.
Make gravy from leftover soup after chicken is removed.
Use leftover flour mixture for thickening.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Put prepared (washed, stemmed and mashed) berries in a pot, add Sure-Jell and stir.
Put on stove and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and bring to a rolling boil; boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Skim off top foam with large spoon. Put into jars and seal.

title: cajun nuggets
directions: Combine soup, bread crumbs and spices.
Dip chicken in crumb mixture coating well.
Place in lightly greased large shallow pan and drizzle with butter.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Turn once during baking.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: soft gingersnaps
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Beat in molasses. Combine the flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, cloves, salt and nutmeg; gradually add to creamed mixture. Refrigerate for 1 hour or until dough is easy to handle. Roll into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar. Place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes or until puffy and lightly browned. Cool for 1 minute before removing to wire racks. Yield: 11 dozen.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, meal and cornstarch.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add butter, lemon juice and rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cutlets in marinara sauce
directions: Lightly saute chicken breasts on both sides in olive oil. Spread in pan and top with sauce and Mozzarella and oregano.
Cook for 15 to 30 minutes, but in the last 5 minutes add fresh basil and parsley.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: spunky tomato juice
directions: Combine all ingredients. Boil thoroughly. Pour hot juice into 8 sterilized quart jars. Secure lids and rings; process jars in a pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure for 20 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine squash, onion and water in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until squash and onion are tender.
Drain well and mash.
Combine squash mixture and remaining ingredients, stirring well. Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and picante sauce together and refrigerate for couple of hours or until thickened.
Spread out on platter. Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onion and cheese.
Place chips on outer edge of platter and serve.

title: nancy's beans
directions: Drain lima, butter and kidney beans.
Cut up and fry bacon. Drain.
Save a small amount of bacon drippings (about 3 tablespoons).
In a large casserole, mix beans and bacon.
Brown onion in bacon drippings.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook to slightly thicken.
Add to beans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Freezes well. Can make sauce ahead and store in refrigerator.

title: shipwreck
directions: In buttered oblong baking dish, place: 1 layer raw potatoes (sliced), 1 layer raw onion (sliced), 1 pound hamburg, 2 handfuls of Minute rice, salt and pepper (layer of each).
Pour over this 1 can kidney beans and 1 can tomato soup (undiluted).
Sprinkle with chili powder and grated cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a casserole dish. Place the pork chops in the dish and cover them with the soup, then add the water.
Cover the dish and cook for 30 to 40 minutes until the chops are cooked through.
Add the pepper and salt to taste.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Begin by browning ground meat and onion; drain. Add cut up potatoes, corn (don't drain), Ro-Tel tomatoes (don't drain), water and chili powder. Bring to a boil and let simmer for 30 minutes.

title: resa's mexican chicken
directions: Cook chicken in pressure cooker or boil, then tear all meat off bones and dice.
Mix soups and Ro-Tel together and 1/2 cup of chicken broth.
Layer in a 13 x 9-inch pan the chips, chicken and sauce; repeat this one time and then top with chips and add a layer of Velveeta cheese.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Alternate beans, sugar and mustard mixture. Put uncooked bacon on top. Top with ketchup. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: fat-free croutons
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch slices.
Sprinkle with Butter Buds, covering completely.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Turn and sprinkle other side.
Cut into crouton size pieces.
Put into brownie tin and cook at 350° for about 20 minutes or until golden in color. Absolutely the very best for salads, soups and just munching!

title: tortellini soup
directions: Brown garlic in margarine.
Add broth and tomatoes and simmer 15 minutes.
Bring to boil; add tortellini.
Reduce heat and simmer 7 minutes more.
Add spinach, basil and cheese.
Simmer a few more minutes.
Serve hot with extra Parmesan.

title: buttermilk salad dressing
directions: Mix and chill; use as dip or salad dressing.

title: garlic grits(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Pour grits into boiling water.
Cook until done.
Add butter and cheese roll to grits.
Stir until melted.
Beat eggs with milk and slowly stir into grits.
Pour into greased baking dish and top with buttered corn flakes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled drumsticks
directions: Heat oil in large nonstick skillet.
Add chicken; brown on all sides, removing drumsticks to plate as they brown.
Add onion, carrot and celery to drippings in skillet; cook, stirring, until softened, about 2 minutes.
Add water, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Return chicken to skillet.
Lower heat; cover and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink near bone.

title: friendship bread
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Grease 2 large loaf pans.
Bake 325° for 1 hour.
Good with a bit of icing drizzled over top.

title: cinnamon dinner rolls
directions: Stir first 7 ingredients together, except only add 3 cups of flour at first.
Mix until smooth.
Add 3 cups remaining flour. Work in and knead in bowl.
Shape.
Add a small amount of oil and round up in the same bowl.
Cover with clear plastic wrap and wet cloth.
Place in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour.

title: awesome slow cooker pot roast
directions: Place the mushroom soups into a slow cooker.
Add the onion soup mix and the water and mix well.
Add the pot roast, flipping several times in the soup mixture to coat all sides of the roast. Cook on high setting for 3 to 4 hours OR on low setting for 8 to 9 hours.

title: oreo mess
directions: Break up cookies in a medium mixing bowl (don't chop). In a large mixing bowl, mix Cool Whip and condensed milk, then fold in cookies (do
not mix hard).
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter.
Then pour melted butter over all.
Blend well.
Shape into balls or logs.
Melt paraffin and chocolate in double boiler.
Dip cookies into chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.

title: gina's lasagna
directions: I prepare the sauce ahead of time and put it into my crock-pot to simmer about 3 hours ahead of time.
The sauce consists of the hamburger, pork burger, spaghetti sauce, green pepper and onion. This makes the sauce thicker.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion over bottom of baked pastry shell.
Mix eggs, half and half, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Pour over ingredients in the pastry shell.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave oven for 9 1/2 to 11 minutes or until set; rotate the pie 1/4 turn once.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: jiffy banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, bananas, biscuit mix and nuts.
Beat until well mixed.
Grease and flour pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake until done.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all together, add chicken broth to give moisture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Cook beef roast; cut into small pieces.
Combine other ingredients; cook until thick.
Add beef to sauce and simmer.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix in order listed.
Put in large bowl; refrigerate.
Cover with Saran Wrap.
Will keep a week.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute onion, garlic and margarine.
Add broth and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Add bacon. Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add half and half.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: mama sue's nacho dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium size bowl.
Cover and chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with Tostitos type corn chips. Will feed 2 starving men or 4 hungry guests or 6 polite people.

title: lemon curd
directions: Grate and squeeze lemons.
Put juice and rind in pot with sugar and margarine. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Beat eggs and add to lemon mixture.
Cook for 10 minutes, very slowly, stirring all the time to prevent curdling.
Cool and fill jars. Put on toast, biscuits, etc., in the morning.

title: shrimp broccoli over rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add shrimp and cooked broccoli.
Add garlic pepper and basil to taste.
Saute all ingredients until hot. Don't overcook or the shrimp will be rubbery.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: arroz con pollo(chicken and rice casserole)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Season chicken with salt, pepper, cumin and oregano.
Heat oil in skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken pieces and brown on all sides.
Remove pieces to baking dish and set aside, keeping warm.

title: ron's chili
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add the celery and onions.
Add some water and cook until soft.
Add the kidney beans, tomato juice, tomato sauce, bay leaves, cloves, salt and pepper.
Simmer in a large pot 4 or 5 hours.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken. Fold in the cream, whipped.
Cover bottom of 9-inch pan (or 9 x 13-inch pan) with half the torn angel food; pour half of the strawberry and cream mixture; make another layer of rest of the torn cake.
Pour remaining strawberry and cream mixture. Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours to set.
Cut into squares.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: kahlua zebras
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and 2 tablespoons butter/margarine.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Set aside.

title: molasses crinkles
directions: Cream shortening; add brown sugar.
Blend in egg and molasses. Sift and measure flour, salt, soda, cloves, ginger and cinnamon; stir in cream mixture.

Mix well and chill 1 hour or overnight. Shape into balls size of walnuts and dip top in granulated sugar. Place, sugar top up, about 3 inches apart on greased baking sheet. On each, drop 2 to 3 drops of water.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: zucchini pancakes(yields 4 servings)
directions: Squeeze excess water out of grated zucchini (press dry between paper towels).
Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Melt 1 tablespoon butter in skillet.
Spoon 2 heaping tablespoons mixture into skillet and flatten with spatula.
Brown both sides on medium heat.
Serve warm with sour cream.
Enjoy!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and celery; mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts over pie filling.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Mix melted butter, flour and sugar together. Then stir in remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls and refrigerate for 3-4 hours.
Cook at 350° for 12-15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: pineapple salad dressing
directions: Heat all except whipped cream.
Cook until thick.
Cool; add whipped cream.
Use on any fruit mixture.
Also good on sponge cake as a dessert.

title: applesauce no egg cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together thoroughly.
Heat applesauce and butter together until butter is melted.
Mix with dry ingredients. Add nuts and/or raisins if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cut chicken into cubes and saute in butter.
Place thawed broccoli on bottom of baking dish.
Next, spread sauteed chicken cubes over broccoli.
Pour Cheddar soup (undiluted) across the chicken.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: indian stew
directions: Brown beef, pepper and onion
together.
Drain grease; add flour and stir well.
Add the sugar, corn, tomatoes, soup and water.
Simmer for 40 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: fresh tomato relish
directions: Chop tomatoes, peppers and onions.
Drain slightly and place in medium bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to mix well. Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with ham, pork, eggs, chicken, shrimp and fish.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Mix everything, stuffing last. Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased casserole dish.

title: seven layer bars
directions: Melt butter and place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer next 5 ingredients in order given.
Pat down.
Pour milk over all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cuts best while warm.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and slice thin.
Chop onions and add to cucumbers.
Sprinkle salt over cucumbers and onions; let stand 3 hours, then drain.

title: microwave ground beef stroganoff
directions: Place ground beef in a 2-quart microwave casserole; break up with fork.
stir in onion and garlic.
Cover and cook on High 5 to 6 minutes, or until beef is no longer red and onion is transparent; drain.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, tomato paste, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on High 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once. Stir in sour cream.
Cook on 60 for 1 minute.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: grandma eleanor's american chop suey
directions: Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions.
Brown ground beef; saute onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and heat.

title: cran-apple salad
directions: Place cranberry sauce in a glass dish or casserole.
Mash with a fork.
Grate apple (using amount desired) over cranberry sauce and stir in.
Spread with desired amount of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with desired amount of nuts.
Refrigerate for a soft salad or freeze for a solid salad.

title: steak pizzaola
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Heat oil in skillet.
Sear steak on high heat.
Remove from skillet to warm dish and lower heat.
Cook onions and garlic until transparent.
Add stock, tomato, spices and heat.
Return steak to pan and cook steak in sauce, long enough to tenderize meat.
This sauce may also be used for braising an eye of round which has been rubbed with garlic and seasoned with salt and pepper.
When tender, slice and serve.

title: 90 minute soft pretzels
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, 2 tablespoons sugar, 1 teaspoon salt and yeast.
Add and beat for 2 minutes:
1 cup warm water and 1 tablespoon margarine or oil (120° to 130°).
Add 1/2 cup flour to mixture and beat 2 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups flour gradually to make soft dough; knead 5 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix cucumber slices with salt and let stand for 2 hours. Drain.
Add onion.
Combine vinegar, sugar and celery seed.
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Refrigerate.
These pickles also freeze well.

title: cocktail franks in chafing dish
directions: Cook franks in boiling water for 2 minutes.
Drain and place in chafing dish.
In small saucepan, combine chili sauce, sweet pickle relish, water and celery seed; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until hot and well blended.
Pour over franks.
Keep warm in chafing dish.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: chicken and rice dish
directions: In a long casserole dish, pour in rice; salt to taste.
Cut up chicken into bite-size and place on top of rice.
Mix cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour over the chicken and rice.
Lay thin patties of butter on top.
Bake in oven at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Pour marshmallows and pecans into pan.
Melt chocolate chips over low heat.
Add milk, butter and vanilla; stir until blended.
Pour chocolate over marshmallows and nuts.
Be sure it is poured evenly.
Let chill for 1 hour.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in a grease and floured pan at 350° until tests done.

title: aunt joy's cheesecake
directions: Grease with margarine the bottom and sides of a cheesecake pan.
Mix cracker crumbs, 1 cup sugar and melted margarine together.
Pat down firmly in pan and put in freezer while making the rest of the cake.

title: neptune's favorite
directions: Place fillets in 9-inch buttered baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt.
Top fillets with green pepper and onion.
Pour white wine into baking pan and bake at 375° for 18 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Pour off cooking liquid.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs and broil 3 inches from heat until cheese melts and bread crumbs are lightly browned (about 2 minutes). Serves 4.

title: quick and easy breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up the 4 slices of bread and place in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Brown the sausage and drain off fat. Sprinkle sausage over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle the shredded cheese over sausage.
Beat together the eggs, milk and salt.
Pour over mixture.
Cheese comes to the top during baking.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Can prepare night before.
Cover.
Refrigerate and bake next morning.

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Cook slowly until thick.
