title: bran muffins
directions: Mix Nabisco 100% Bran with boiling water; set aside.
Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs; then add buttermilk.
Add water/bran mixture.
Sift flour with soda and salt; add to mixture.
Add All-Bran.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Large muffins will take longer.
This recipe makes 1 gallon and will keep several weeks in refrigerator.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, mix rice, cream soup and water.
Lay sectioned chicken on top of rice mixture. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over all.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with your favorite vegetable and you have a meal for 4.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown the
ground beef and drain. Add the beans, Ro-Tel tomatoes and
soup.
Put
layer of Doritos in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour
beef mixture over Doritos.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: friendship tea
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Add 1 tablespoon mixture to 1 cup hot water in mug for each serving.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel eggplant, slice, chop and boil in water with a little salt, until tender.
Mash eggplant and drain off water or extra liquid.
Beat egg and milk together.
In a casserole dish approximately 9-inches square or round pour 1/2 of eggplant.
Add 1/2 of the cracker crumbs and 1/2 of the cheese and 1/2 the egg/milk.
Pour rest of eggplant in and add cracker crumbs, milk and egg and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 45 minutes, until knife comes out clean.
Eat immediately; not as good warmed over.

title: pear preserves
directions: Wash, pare and core pears.
Run through grinder or processor until fine.
Measure out 4 1/2 cups.
Mix with 1 box of Sure-Jell. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
Add all at once, 5 cups sugar and teaspoon of allspice or cinnamon.
Bring to full rolling boil again and time 1 minute, stirring constantly. Cool 5 minutes.
Skim foam and seal into sterile jars.
Can process 10 minutes in boiling water bath for safety.
Makes 4 pints.

title: spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brown crust according to directions on package.
Mix all ingredients in bowl except one egg.
Pour into browned pie crust and bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven, add pie top and brush with beaten egg.
Bake for an additional 10 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: stir-fried vegetables with pasta
directions: In a skillet or wok, saute onion, celery, pepper, zucchini, broccoli and asparagus in butter until tender-crisp.
Do not overcook.
Add mushrooms, tomatoes, cheese and spices.
Stir until thoroughly heated.
Do not overcook.
Serve immediately on hot buttered pasta and sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: hodge podge soup
directions: Brown the beef and onion.
Drain off fat, if needed. Add all other ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients and 1 cup water. Simmer, covered, 15 minutes; stir often.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella cheese.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Melt margarine in pie plate in oven; brush the sides.
Beat eggs slightly with whisk.
Beat in remaining ingredients (do not overbeat).
Pour into pie plate. Bake 25 to 30 minutes until puffy and deep golden brown.
Serve with powdered sugar or mixed fruit.

title: birthday cake icing
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Mix with mixer; add vanilla and mix well.
Keep covered until ready to spread on cake. Food coloring may be added for decorating.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or just until center of custard is set.
Stir once in first 20 minutes of baking.

title: carne asada(mexican barbecue)
directions: Cut meat into serving pieces.
Place in glass bowl or dish. Combine remaining ingredients as a marinade, slicing lemon into eight pieces, squeezing over meat.
Mix all ingredients, lemon pieces, meat and marinade in bowl.
Marinate 6 hours or overnight. Grill (barbecue) or broil to your favorite doneness.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Boil sugar, milk and oleo for 1 minute.
Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, quick rolled oats, cocoa and vanilla.
Drop on waxed paper.

title: fruit salad
directions: Place fruit in bowl.
Mix ingredients and cook until thickens.
Pour over fruit.
Mix gently and refrigerate in covered dish overnight when possible.

title: mt. dew punch
directions: Mix well and serve over crushed ice.

title: sausage loaf
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In large greased casserole, place diced chicken.
Mix soups with undiluted evaporated milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix the stuffing mix and spread evenly over top.
Heat broth with oleo until melted and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into buttered square pan and cool and cut in squares.

title: brunch ambrosia
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cover and chill 1 hour. Arrange fruit in individual serving dishes; sprinkle with coconut and garnish with mint, if desired.

title: glazed pork roast
directions: Half cook roast.
Then place potatoes and onions in baker. Salt and pepper to taste.
The apple juice gives the roast a glazed texture.
Cook at 350 degrees until done.
Baby carrots are optional if you like.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar and butter.
Stir well.
Stir in milk, egg yolks, vanilla and nutmeg.
Set aside.

title: potato puff(make ahead)
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients. Fold in the eggs. Refrigerate or bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in 3-quart dish.
Combine cream cheese, milk, salt, garlic powder and 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese in saucepan and cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle additional Parmesan cheese over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: taglerene
directions: Brown ground chuck; add onion, bell pepper, chili powder, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add sliced olives and juice.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and corn.
Drain noodles and add to sauce if pan is big enough; if not, line dishes with noodles and pour sauce over.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° until bubbly (about 30 minutes or more).
Can freeze.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook on low all day.
Serve on toasted bun.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes until done.
While still warm, cut up the potatoes. Fry the bacon crisp. Remove from grease.
Saute onions in bacon grease.
Pour grease and onions over the potatoes. Crumble up bacon.
Mix up in potatoes.
Add dressing.
Mix up.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Test with knife in center for doneness.

title: nachos
directions: Spread chips with bean dip and guacamole.
Top with peppers and cheese.
Arrange on serving plate.
Cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Repeat procedure as directed.

title: ice water pickles
directions: Put vegetables in a Dutch oven.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with crushed ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain and pour vinegar solution over them after it has come to a boil.
Keep in refrigerator in a large container/jar.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix.
Place in glass baking dish or roaster.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.

title: pickled meat or fish
directions: Cook meat or fish until tender; drain off juice and keep.
Cut meat into small pieces.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Boil meat or fish for 30 minutes in brine.
Add 2 cups broth; cool. Let stand 3 days.
Can be put into jars and sealed.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cake
directions: In large bowl, pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs. Sift together then add
flour, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread remaining chips and walnuts or pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: tomato french dressing
directions: Beat all ingredients, except onion, in a bowl briskly.
(Beat hard and will not separate.)
Place in jar with cover; add onion. Garnish can also be used but remove before using the dressing.

title: cherry delight
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix Dream Whip according to instructions.
Blend cream cheese and Dream Whip until smooth. Slowly mix 1/2 cup sugar into mixture.
Refrigerate
30 minutes. Add 1 can cherry pie filling to the top.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Make roux with flour and oil.
Add vegetables.
Cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook 20 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and red pepper.
Add shrimp.
Cook slowly until tender. Serve over rice.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Place cabbage in bottom of buttered 8-inch casserole dish. Combine cream, eggs, sugar and salt.
Pour over cabbage.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red cocoa cake
directions: Put boiling water on cocoa.
Add soda and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture.

title: shrimp pilou
directions: Melt butter and stir in all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: broccoli delight salad
directions: Put washed, well drained broccoli pieces in large glass bowl. Add raisins, onion, bacon and sunflower seeds.
Mix together 3 to 4 tablespoons sugar, 1/2 cup lite mayonnaise and 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Pour over salad.
Toss well.
Makes 6 servings.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease bottom of square cake pan.
Add coconut and pecans. Press in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
Heat butter and cream cheese. Mix in confectioners sugar.
Pour all over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
D-e-l-i-c-i-o-u-s.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel, cube and boil potatoes until tender, but still firm. Drain.
Hard-boil eggs, peel and chop.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil and drain potatoes.
Put in casserole dish.
Spray dish with Pam.
Melt margarine.
Add flour; add milk, salt and pepper. When thick, pour over potatoes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken and grill.
Cube cooked chicken.
Chop cabbage.
Crumble dry, uncooked noodles.
Combine in a large bowl with peas, seeds and noodles.
Mix last four ingredients and pour over salad.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: tuna broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and place in shallow 2-quart casserole.
Add tuna and cover with diluted mushroom soup.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Add bread crumbs to melted butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serves 5.

title: fast fruit cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a 2-quart baking dish.
Stir in milk and vanilla to make a thin batter.
Place fruit over the batter and drizzle the melted butter over the top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until nicely browned. (Try cherries, berries or fruit in season.)

title: pizza cobbler(easy enough for kids to make!)
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan with vegetable oil. Place about 1/4 of the pizza sauce in the bottom of the pan. Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces. Roll pieces into balls and place on top of sauce in the pan. Pour remaining sauce over biscuits. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and a dusting of your favorite herbs (i.e, parsley, oregano, garlic, etc.). Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve warm.

title: scotch cookies
directions: Roll out and cut with tumbler.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, frost and put 1/2 cherry on top.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water.
Set aside.
Boil until thick the egg yolks, pineapple and sugar.
When thick, add gelatin; cook a few minutes longer.
Remove from stove and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 1 cup sugar, little at a time.
Add vanilla and salt; fold the 1st ingredients into egg whites.
Let cool slightly.
Put into graham cracker crust.
Use one package of crackers and about 1/4 of butter or oleo, melted.
Put into a 2-quart square glass pan.
Hold back about 1/2 cup of crackers. Pour top ingredients on crust.
Put the 1/2 cup crackers on top of this.
Add cherries on top of crackers.
This is rich, will serve about 18.
Makes a pretty dessert.
That 18, depends on how big you cut it.

title: pineapple orange creme
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter. Reserve 1/3 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumb mixture in ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In mixer bowl, beat dry milk, orange juice and egg white on high speed 3 minutes. Add lemon juice. Beat 3 minutes on high speed. Blend in sugar on low speed, about 1/2 minute. Fold in pineapple.
Pour into pan. Sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture. Freeze at least 8 hours.

title: chocolate banana cake
directions: Place chocolate
in
top of a double boiler; bring water to a boil.
Reduce
heat
to
low; cook until chocolate melts. Set aside to
cool.
Cream butter, gradually add sugar, beating well with
an
electric
mixer.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after
each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt;
add
to
creamed
mixture
alternately with banana, buttermilk
and
melted
chocolate,
beginning
and ending with flour mixture.
Mix
well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Spoon batter into
(9-inch) greased and floured round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick
inserted
in center comes out
clean.
Cool
in
pans
10 minutes;
remove from pan and
cool
completely.
Spread Chocolate Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.

title: jackstraw eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into finger size strips.
Combine 1 cup flour, water, egg, 2 tablespoons vegetable oil, sugar and salt; mix well.
Dredge strips in additional flour, then dip in batter. Fry strips in hot oil (375°) until golden brown; drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve hot.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: cherry pie cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Pour in greased pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Cut butter into chunks and put on top.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together cream of chicken soup, cream of celery soup, water and Veg-All.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: cheesy broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package, using only 3 Tbsp margarine.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients in 2 quart casserole dish; top with stuffing.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: sweet -n- sour wieners
directions: Put jelly in crock-pot, liquify and add mustard.
Put wieners in and simmer for 6 hours.

title: cream cheese swirl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of square pan.
Beat cream cheese and milk on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Spread evenly in pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over brownie batter.
Marble by pulling knife through batter in curves; turn pan and repeat.
Bake 28 to 30 minutes; cool completely.
Refrigerate any remaining brownies.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg. Add molasses and dry ingredients. Roll into balls. Dip into sugar. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: quick goulash
directions: Cook up Top Ramen soup in 3 cups of water, then add all remainder of ingredients, stirring it a little, bring to a simmer. Remove from heat and serve in bowls, topped with grated cheese (optional).
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake with apple pie
directions: Mix together the ingredients of the 2 bowls.
Bake in tube pan for 60 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet and sour apricot glazed chicken thighs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pat chicken dry. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Place chicken, skin side up, in a 13 x 9 x 2 dish. Combine apricot jam, chili sauce and mustard in a small bowl. Force mixture through a small strainer with the back of a spoon. Bake in the preheated oven for 25 minutes. Brush skin side of chicken with half the apricot glaze. Bake 20 minutes more or until tender, brushing with the remaining glaze. Serve on a bed of hot cooked rice, mixed with almond slivers and chopped parsley.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 350° for 1 hour or until very soft. Cool slightly. Cut potatoes in half; scoop out the pulp and discard shells. Place pulp in food processor or blender; cover and process until smooth.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries and break apart with fork as they melt.
Do not mash berries.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture into dish and chill until firm.
Spread top of this with sour cream.
Spoon remaining jello mixture over sour cream and chill.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend, chill and roll to 1/4 inch on slightly floured board. Cut with cookie cutter.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Sprinkle with peanuts.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: corn and green chiles
directions: Empty corn and chiles in a baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients, melting them down.
Pour over corn, mixing well. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Heat milk and add to mixture.
Beat egg yolks and add to above.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over crumb crust and top with a meringue or Cool Whip.
(I top with a meringue.
I use 2 tablespoons sugar to one egg white.)

title: meatballs
directions: Mix well and form into balls.
Roll in flour and brown in a deep fryer or in a large skillet.
Take out and simmer in 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1/2 can of water for 20 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix graham crackers, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine and press onto bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cream cheese until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time. Mix well.
Blend in chips and vanilla.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for about an hour (use your judgment).
Loosen cake from rim. Cool completely.
Remove rim.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add unbeaten egg yolks one at a time, beating thoroughly each time.
Add vanilla, flour, salt and baking powder.
Put through a cookie press.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 12 dozen cookies.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: In small bowl combine sour cream, honey, lime juice and nutmeg to make the dressing.
Blend well and refrigerate.
Clean the spinach and tear it into bite size pieces.
Clean the strawberries and slice them in half.
Gently toss spinach and berries in serving bowl.
Add the dressing and toss slightly.
Garnish with the coconut.
Dressing can be served on the side if desired.

title: raspberry chicken
directions: Melt butter and brown chicken on both sides over medium-high heat.
Remove from skillet.
Add onion to the drippings in the pan and cook, covered, over low heat until tender, about 15 minutes. Add vinegar; raise heat and cook, uncovered, until vinegar is reduced to a syrupy spoonful.
Whisk in chicken stock and simmer about 1 minute.
Return chicken to skillet and simmer gently in sauce, basting often, until done.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from water and cool.
Mix water, butter, brown sugar and salt in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for a full 3 minutes.
(You must keep syrup boiling for a full 3 minutes.)
Pour syrup in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Grease cake pan with margarine.
Mix both cans of soup with uncooked rice and put in bottom of pan.
Put uncooked chicken on top of rice.
Do not add any seasonings.
Sprinkle a package of dry Lipton onion soup mix over the chicken.
You may add 1/2 cup milk to the rice mixture.
Wrap entire pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not look until done.

title: honey salad dressing
directions: Mix salad dressing and evaporated milk; stir until smooth. Add lemon juice, honey and celery seed.
Mix well and chill.
Good on fruit salad.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Mix bread crumbs with cheese and parsley.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine, then bread crumbs. Place dipped chicken on a rack on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems.
Wash, pat dry and brush caps with part of melted butter.
Combine rest of butter with garlic powder.	Add cheese and onions (or dip mix).
Mix well.	Add soy sauce, wine and crumbs.
Chopped stems can be added also.
Fill caps.
Top with cheese if desired.
Put on cookie sheet and broil 3 to 5 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine and bake about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: microwave dog biscuits
directions: Mix the flours, nonfat milk powder, wheat germ and corn meal. Add the honey and garlic powder, mix until crumbly.
Add the beaten egg, gradually add canned beef broth, mixing until dough is like pie dough.
May need to add some water or might not use all the broth.
Roll dough out onto well floured board.
Use cookie cutters.
Cut out shapes.
Place on microwave-safe plate. Microwave at Medium 5 to 10 minutes until firm and dry.
Rotate plate and turn treats over every 2 minutes.
Watch carefully, microwaves vary in their heat settings.
Cool on wire rack. Cookies crisp as they cool.
May roll dough into log shapes.
May take 8 to 12 minutes.

title: cauliflower and broccoli salad
directions: Combine vegetables and toss well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: sweet potatoes and topping
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in greased casserole dish.

title: english tea scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease large baking sheet.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cream of tartar.
Blend with pastry blender or 2 knives; cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Beat half and half and egg.
Measure out and reserve 2 tablespoons.
Add remaining egg mixture to dry ingredients with raisins.
Mix lightly until it clings together and forms soft dough.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mash beans with fork.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended; refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: salmon party balls
directions: Drain and flake salmon, removing skin and bones.
Combine salmon with next 5 ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Chill and shape into a ball.
Roll in mixture of nuts and parsley.

title: six-weeks muffins
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and sugar together.
Add Raisin Bran; mix well.
Beat the eggs; pour into flour mixture.
Add buttermilk and cooking oil; stir well.
Fill muffin pans (greased and floured) 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: springtime skillet dinner
directions: Brown garlic in hot skillet; add onions and beef.
Cook until brown, stirring occasionally.
Add carrots, rice, water and simmer uncovered over low heat about 40 minutes.
Add potatoes, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Continue to simmer until done (about 20 minutes).

title: banana cream pie
directions: For filling, in a medium saucepan, combine sugar, flour or cornstarch and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Separate egg yolks from whites. Set whites aside for meringue.
Beat egg yolk slightly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of the hot mixture into yolks.
Return egg mixture to saucepan.
Bring to a gentle boil.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter or margarine and vanilla.
Slice 3 bananas into bottom of pastry shell.
Pour hot filling into baked pastry shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling.
Seal to edge. Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool. Cover; chill to store.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sunshine muffins
directions: Beat egg and milk.
Stir in pineapple and margarine.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and 1/4 cup sugar.
Add to pineapple mixture, stirring only until moistened.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and orange rind.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven approximately 25 minutes. Yield:
12 muffins; 155 calories per muffin.

title: souffle sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes, sugar, butter, vanilla and nutmeg in large mixing bowl; beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Place in souffle dish or 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve while hot.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat peanut butter with cream cheese until well mixed.
Beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Fold in thawed topping.
Spoon into crust and chill.
Can be frozen.
Serves six.

title: italian zucchini pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onions until tender. Stir in parsley and seasonings. In a large bowl, blend cheese and eggs. Stir in vegetable mix. Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in ungreased 11-inch quiche pan or 10-inch baking dish or 12 x 8-inch dish. Press over bottom and sides to form crust. Spread crust with mustard.
Pour vegetable mix into crust. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: potato soup
directions: Make "flaked noodles" but adding enough flour, all at once, to beaten egg.
Work with fingers or fork until flaky and in small pieces.
Brown bacon.
Cook potatoes, celery and onion in water with salt and pepper added.
When boiling good add "noodles" and bacon.
You may have to add more water or use only 1/2 of "noodles."
The rest can be frozen.
Stir often.
Add water for consistency you like.
Cook about 20 minutes.
Add 1 cup of powdered milk mixed with a little water.
Heat slowly until hot. Will scorch easily.
Add clams and you have chowder.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix bourbon and nuts in covered dish and refrigerate overnight.
Mix sugar, butter, vanilla and bourbon-nut mixture until well blended.
Return to refrigerator for at least 2 hours. Roll into balls, return to refrigerator.
When chocolate bits and paraffin is melted in double-boiler, dip balls in chocolate-paraffin mixture one at a time.
Place on wax paper. When balls have hardened, store in covered container in refrigerator.

title: white chili
directions: Cook and prepare chicken.
Mix all ingredients in a large pot or crock-pot except the hot pepper sauce and cheese.
Cook for about an hour or so.
If using crock-pot, let cook on low all day. May have to add a little water.
When serving, add hot pepper sauce to taste and garnish with shredded cheese.
Makes about 8 main dish servings.

title: mercedes tamale pie
directions: Saute carrots, celery, onion and green pepper together.
Mix with whole corn, creamed corn, corn meal, salt to taste and cumin. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and serve cold.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Mix flour and oleo.
Pat to a thin crust in oblong dish.
Bake 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Set aside to cool.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Slice chicken meat into thin strips.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon cornstarch, the pepper, 1 tablespoon oil, the salt and 1 teaspoon soy sauce.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Cut pineapple into small wedges.

title: cotton pickin' good cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into three 8-inch cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before icing.

title: divinity
directions: Cook to hard ball stage, 260°.
While that is cooking, beat 2 egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Pour mixture over egg whites and beat at high speed until it holds its shape, 4 to 5 minutes. Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch square pan or drop by spoonfuls on greased wax paper.

title: diabetic cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop in mounds.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: harvey house coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage, onion and green pepper and mix with cup of sugar.
Boil together next 6 ingredients.
Bring to full boil. Pour over cabbage mixture.
Let stand at least 2 hours before using.
Keeps
up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and bone salmon and flake with fork.
Mix all other ingredients with salmon; form loaf in bread pan.
Flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: bailey's fudge sauce
directions: Slowly melt butter and chocolate in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and add sugar and evaporated milk alternately.
Stir until smooth.
Return to heat; simmer 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix the ingredients together, using only 1 cup of chopped pecans in mixture.
Roll in ball and then roll ball in 1 cup crushed pecans.
Serve on Sociables crackers.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain juice off fruit; mix all ingredients in large bowl and refrigerate.
Serve when chilled.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Boil raisins, dates and apples in water for 3 minutes.
Add shortening to melt, then cool.
Add rest of ingredients with nuts last.
Mix well and refrigerate until well chilled.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 10 to 12 minutes. Refrigerate in airtight container.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix well and add 2/3 cup red wine vinegar.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rich dinner rolls
directions: Soak yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
Pour milk over sugar and salt in a large bowl.
Stir until dissolved.
Beat in 1 cup flour, shortening, eggs and yeast mixture.
Add remaining flour to make a soft dough.
When dough leaves sides of bowl, turn out onto a lightly floured board (counter).
Knead until dough becomes smooth and elastic.
Place in a lightly greased bowl.
Grease top of dough.
Cover with waxed paper.

title: e-z hamburger casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in casserole.
Top with more cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili verde
directions: Cut pork into 3-inch cubes and saute in oil in small batches until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and saute onions, garlic and green pepper.
Return meat to pan.
Add rest of ingredients and salt and pepper to taste plus dash of red pepper flakes.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (1 to 2 hours) and sauce is rich and thick.
Add water during cooking if necessary.
Spoon onto hot tortillas with a dollop of sour cream and squeeze of lime juice. Roll up to eat.

title: beef dish - japanese style
directions: Trim fat from beef and cut up into pieces a little larger than bite size.
Brown quickly, cover and simmer on low heat for about 1 hour.
Do not add any liquids.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Brown rice and mushrooms in butter.
Add soup and water. Cover and simmer 20 to 35 minutes, depending on degree of moisture desired.
Serves 4.
Great with roast beef!

title: caramel chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sprinkle pecans evenly over unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and drizzle with caramel topping. Set aside.

title: peach pie
directions: Pour ingredients over sliced peaches in 9-inch pie crust. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 35 minutes or until set and lightly browned.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Cook hamburger and onion in large pot until done.
Add salt and pepper, tomato juice, tomato paste, whole tomatoes, sliced mushrooms, oregano, Italian seasoning, red pepper, parsley flakes and sugar.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with cooking spray.
Put rice in dish and spread evenly on bottom.
Mix water and soup together; pour 1/2 of mixture on rice and put 1/2 of Lipton soup mix over soup.
Lay chicken breasts over rice mixture.
Put remaining soup mix and Lipton soup over chicken.
Salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pralines
directions: In heavy, 4-quart pan, combine sugars, baking soda, milk and salt.
Boil over moderate heat until it reaches thread stage (230°).
Remove from heat.
Add butter, nuts and vanilla.
Beat candy until it starts to become thick and slightly sugary.
Then place pan over low heat to prevent candy from becoming too hard.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 400° in uncovered pan for approximately 2 hours.

title: herb-roasted capon
directions: Remove giblets and neck from inside bird.
Rinse bird with running cold water and drain well.
Combine seasoned salt, thyme, rosemary, sage, pepper and garlic powder and rub over outside and into body cavity.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight.
Brush skin with oil; roast uncovered in 325° oven 3 to 4 hours, basting frequently.
Makes 8 servings.

title: salad delight
directions: Mix in large bowl until well blended.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: polish kielbasa, rice and beans
directions: Brown sausage, onion and green pepper in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice or mix the rice into mixture (2 to 3 cups rice).

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain and mash.
Season with salt and pepper. Add other ingredients, except herb dressing and butter.
Melt butter in oblong casserole dish.
Stir in 3/4 of herb dressing mix.
Mix until butter is absorbed.
Combine with squash mixture. Pour into casserole dish and cover with herb dressing.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Pour dry pudding mix over drained pineapple.
Add marshmallows, pecans and Cool Whip.
Mix together and chill several hours.

title: diabetic mincemeat
directions: Grind together ground beef and suet.
Combine all ingredients. Cook slowly 3 to 4 hours.

title: seafood gumbo
directions: Brown onion and celery in oil for 1 minute.
Mash tomatoes. Add to onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add water to make 2 quarts of gravy.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Chop vegetables.
Sprinkle
salt
over	cabbage and let stand 12 hours.
Squeeze	cabbage dry and add celery and green pepper. Mix
vinegar,
water,
sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Bring to a boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Cool.
Pour cooled dressing mixture
over
vegetables.	Mix well.
Put in freezer containers and
freeze.
Thaw	to serve.
This keeps a nice crunch.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, pepper and celery until soft.
Add remaining ingredients; blend and simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: potato rolls
directions: Put water in big mixing bowl.
Stir in yeast.
Add sugar, salt, Crisco, eggs and potatoes, then add flour.
Mix together. Put in bowl to rise and put in refrigerator overnight.
Cover with plastic wrap.
In morning, knead and shape into rolls or roll and cut out.
Butter tops; let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Dough will keep 4 days in refrigerator.
Makes 40 rolls.

title: "earthquake" cookies
directions: Fold whipped topping, beaten egg and vanilla together.
Add cake mix and stir well.
Put powdered sugar in separate bowl. Drop cookie mixture in by teaspoon.
Coat each lightly with the sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheets and bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
When done, the edges are lightly browned and the top has "earthquake" lines.

title: exotic mushroom soup
directions: Heat oil in large skillet and cook the onion for 3 to 4 minutes or until sort and golden.
Wipe each mushroom with damp cloth and cut large mushrooms into small bite-size pieces.
Add mushrooms to skillet, stirring quickly to coat them in the end. Add milk to skillet; bring to a boil.
Cover and leave simmer for 5 minutes.
Gradually stir in hot bouillon.
Under preheated broiler toast the bread on both sides until golden.
Mix together the butter and garlic and spoon generously over toast.
Place toast in bottom of a large tureen or divide between 4 individual serving bowls and pour over the hot soup.
Top with grated cheese and serve at once.

title: red punch
directions: Combine cranberry juice and apple juice in punch bowl. Slowly pour in 7-Up.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together; chill at least one hour before serving. Makes 4 cups.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: In food processor bowl with metal blade, combine all ingredients.
Cover.
Process 30 seconds.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight to blend flavors.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: polish pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and make a hole in the middle of the mixture.
Mix egg, vinegar and water.
Put this mixture in the hole and mix together for pie crust.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Generously grease popover pans or large muffin cups.
In a small bowl, beat eggs lightly. Add flour, salt and milk.
Mix until just blended.
Do not overbeat.
Fill prepared pans half full with batter.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until deep golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until crunchy.
Cook chicken breasts and then cube (can use any cut up chicken or even leftover turkey).
Layer chicken and broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and sherry; pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and croutons.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza rustica or easter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown sausage meat and drain excess fat.
Mix eggs, Ricotta and grated cheese.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Grease a large lasagna pan and pour mix in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Best when settled for 1 day and heat before serving.
Do not serve out of the oven or else the pie will run.
Must be cooled down.

title: stuffed jumbo shells
directions: One hour before serving, prepare shells as label directs; drain well.
Heat salad oil, ground beef, onion, garlic, celery, salt and pepper until meat is well browned.
Stir in walnuts and 1/2 jar spaghetti sauce.
Stuff rounded tablespoonful of meat mixture into each shell.
Reserve remaining meat mixture.
Spoon 1 cup sauce into 10 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with remaining meat mixture.
Spoon remaining sauce evenly in and around shells, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: exotic chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, water chestnuts, celery, grapes and almonds. Mix mayonnaise, curry powder, soy sauce and lemon juice; add to chicken mixture.
Chill for several hours.
Serve on lettuce leaf and top with pineapple chunks.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 300°.
Makes two pies.

title: chicken and ham roll-ups
directions: Boil chicken until done. Then cut chicken in strips. Top each piece with ham and cheese; roll up and secure with toothpicks. Brown roll-ups in skillet with butter. Keep turning until brown. Top with margarine. Place in dish. Pour chicken soup over contents. Cover with foil and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: german sweet sour dressing
directions: Mix all except vinegar together, then add to vinegar.
I sometimes heat this, but it's not necessary.
Add 1 cup salad oil of your choice.
Shake well and refrigerate.
Very good on tossed vegetable salads.
Also used on slaw, potato and macaroni salads using partly along with mayonnaise.

title: pepper pots
directions: Mix all together and shape into balls and bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: american cheese rollercoasters
directions: First, you
put
the
cheese
on top of the bologna and then you roll it up.
Then you eat it.

title: breakfast chile fluff
directions: Beat eggs; add flour and salt, then the rest of ingredients. Pour into 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until firm in middle.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Mix and cook in crock-pot 4 to 6 hours.

title: crock-pot brown beans
directions: Wash beans. Soak the beans overnight with water to top of crock-pot on slow.
Turn to high the next morning and cook all day.
Add chunks of ham and onion. Salt and pepper to taste. Serve with Jiffy corn bread, frozen shredded hash browns, shredded cheese, canned tomatoes, etc.

title: debbie's italian bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice Italian bread in half and place on foil.
Mix scallion, mayonnaise, garlic, seasoning, mushrooms and cheeses.
(It is best if this mixture marinates about 2 hours.)
Spread mixture on bread.
Place bread in oven for approximately 5 minutes until cheese begins to melt. Set oven on broil until cheese is finished melting and bread browns.
Be careful not to burn.
Bread will brown in 1 to 2 minutes. Serve.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Make favorite meat loaf.
Put half in loaf pan.
Place hard-boiled eggs down center.
Cover with rest of mixture.
Make Stove Top dressing.
Put half of meat in loaf pan and put dressing over that.
Cover with rest of meat.
Serve with chicken gravy made with broth.

title: spritz*
directions: Mix butter, sugar, egg, salt and flavoring thoroughly.
Sift flour.
Work into mixture.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Using 1/4 dough, press through cookie press onto baking sheets using desired shapes.
Add sprinkles if desired.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 9 minutes.
Do not brown! Makes 5 dozen.

title: quick cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Spoon cherry pie filling into a pie plate.
In medium bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and cinnamon. With pastry blender, cut butter or margarine into flour mixture until it resembles peas.
Sprinkle over filling.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 375°; bake 10 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: sweet and salty peanut cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Beat eggs and add to butter and sugar. Add flour, salt and soda. Stir in oatmeal, cornflakes and peanuts. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: milk chocolate fudge
directions: Combine milk, margarine, sugar and Marshmallow Creme in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes by the clock after it begins to boil.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until chips are melted.
Pour into a 9-inch square buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli in water; do not drain.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup.
Mix well.
Add rice and broccoli.
Pour mixture in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Casserole can be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to heat.)

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles according to package directions.
Brown meat, stirring to separate.
Add spaghetti sauce, tomato paste, salt, Italian seasoning and garlic.
If desired, allow to simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain any excess liquid from cottage cheese. Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Spoon about 1/3 of meat sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-x 2-inch baking dish or two 9 x 9-inch dishes.
Cover meat with 1/2 of noodles.
Spread noodles with 1/2 of cottage cheese and 1/2 of shredded Mozzarella cheese. Repeat ending with meat sauce.
Sprinkle with extra Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes to set.
Makes 12 (3-inch) servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook meat and onion. Drain. Place 3 cups cabbage in a 2-quart casserole dish. Cover with meat mixture.
Add remaining cabbage. Pour soup over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings. May add 1 cup rice.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Heat oleo in iron skillet and brown ground beef.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: In Dutch oven or large heavy saucepan, lightly brown ground beef.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, vegetables, onion soup mix and sugar.
Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or more.

title: poor man's casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with bell pepper, onion, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Drain grease; add tomato sauce.
Pour mixture into a large casserole.
Put a layer of cheese over the whole mixture. Over this, add the potatoes and seal around the edges.
Sprinkle paprika over potatoes.
Bake in 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In the morning parboil them for 10 minutes with a teaspoon of baking soda.
Then run cold water through the beans in a colander.
Dice rind of salt pork in 1-inch squares.
Cut in half.
Put half in bean pot (bottom).
Put beans in pot.
Put rest of pork on top.
Mix other ingredients with hot water.
Pour over beans.
Put in 300° oven for 6 hours. Add more water when needed.
Uncover for last half hour.

title: mama's old fashion chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook on 300° for approximately 15 minutes and turn up to 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: parsley-garlic sauce
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Place over hot (not boiling) water. Stir with a wire whisk until well blended.
Add butter, 1 T at a time, stirring constantly with wire whisk until butter melts.
Continue whisking until sauce is thickened.
Serve over seafood, beef or vegetables.

title: charles' liver hash
directions: Cook sausage and hamburger together.
Add onions.
Use potato masher to break up lumps.
Add mustard, Tabasco, salt, pepper and liver pudding.
Put vinegar in last, just before you take it off stove.

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Brown ground beef (drain), put in crockpot & add cheese. Stir until melted. Add relish. Cook for 1 hour on low.

title: banana-chocolate chip muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour muffin pans or line with paper.
Mix sugar, egg and butter.
In separate bowl, combine bananas and milk.

title: granny's deviled crabs
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion, celery tops and parsley and saute.
Stir flour into milk.
Add milk mixture to onion mixture, slowly stirring until thickens.
Pour over crabmeat seasoned with paprika and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir together lightly.
Chill slightly.
Form into cakes and pat on more bread crumbs.
Brown on each side in shortening in fry pan until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli and onion. Add stuffing.
Put in 2-quart casserole. Dribble butter on top. Combine soups and spoon over broccoli; do not mix.
Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and continue baking 15 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: wilderness-style apple pie filling
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon juice and apples.
Cook at medium temperature until bubbling.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice.

title: rocky mountain sandwich
directions: Mix all ingredients well and spread on sandwich bread.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook oleo and onion until onion is clear. Add all other ingredients. Cook, uncovered, about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed potato bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Combine the first 6 ingredients in given order. When lukewarm, add yeast and water. Stirring with a large spoon, add enough flour to make a firm dough, not stiff. Place in greased bowl and grease top of dough lightly with oil. Use right away or cover and put in refrigerator. Use within 4 days. Roll in shape; let rise in warm place 1 1/2 hours or until double in size. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until soft.
Cool and peel.
Dice potatoes, eggs and onion.

title: hot rolls(5 dozen)
directions: Mix milk, shortening, sugar and salt together.
Let cool.
Add yeast in warm milk and eggs and mix well.
Add flour and knead well.
Let rise 2 1/2 hours.
Beat down and squeeze dough, through thumb and index fingers, making round balls.
Put in greased round cake pans.
Let rise 2 hours.
Cook at 350°
until brown.
Turn onto foil.
Let cool or serve hot.

title: crock-pot ribs and limas
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs; cut ribs in serving size pieces, if large.
In a large skillet, over medium heat, brown ribs in oil; discard drippings.
Meanwhile, place onion and carrots in crock-pot.
Add ribs.
In a medium bowl, stir brown sugar, flour, dry mustard, salt and pepper until blended.
Stir in water and vinegar until smooth.
Pour over ribs.
Push bay leaf into liquid. Cover and cook on high for 5 to 6 hours on low for 10 to 12 hours or until meat is very tender.
Stir in lima beans.
Immediately cover and cook on high for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.
Remove bay leaf before serving.
Serves 6.

title: kahlua brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together sugar, egg substitute, liqueur and melted margarine until blended.

title: homemade sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process until smooth. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts; remove meat.
Save liquid.
(Use boneless chicken breasts and canned broth.)
Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Put 1/2 of stuffing in bottom of dish. Distribute chicken breasts over crumbs.
Dilute soups with broth. Mix and pour over chicken.
Put remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 6.

title: oven stew beef
directions: Mix together and pour over beef (cut in small cubes).
Stir together.
Bake at 325° for 3 hours, covered.
Served with rice.

title: rotini cucumber salad
directions: Cook rotini according to package direction.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain well!
Place in bowl; add cucumber and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients in blender or jar with tight-fitting lid; mix well.
Pour over rotini mixture and toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for at least an hour before serving. Yield: 4 servings.

title: zucchini stew
directions: Saute the onion in oil. Add tomato sauce and potatoes.
When cooked half way, add green pepper (cut up) and the cut up zucchini. Let cook on low for about 1 hour or until zucchini is tender.

title: quick poppy seed loaf
directions: Combine first
five ingredients in a large mixing bowl, beat well.
Stir in pecans and poppy seed.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5
x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or
until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in
pan 10 minutes, remove from pan and cool on a wire rack. Yields 1 loaf.

title: sand tarts
directions: Beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out small amounts at a time; cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate and bake at 350° for 9 minutes.

title: citrus chops
directions: Heat oil in large skillet. Brown pork chops on both sides over medium heat. Add basil, onions and orange juice. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until chops are cooked through.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix the Hidden Valley mix and the cream cheese together.
Drain olives and chilies (chop or slice); then add to cream cheese with chopped onions.
Spread over flour tortilla shells (5 or 6) and roll up.
Cut with a sharp knife and chill until ready to serve.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream, stirring until well blended.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch square pan and freeze until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: chinese five spice chicken
directions: In bowl combine all ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces, add chicken broth, soup and vegetables.
Mix flour, milk and melted butter together and pour into casserole dish.
Pour the chicken mixture
on top and cook for 35 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: cilantro grilled salmon
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; marinate for at least 2 hours. Broil on hot grill 5 minutes per side.

title: pumpkin ice cream pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, brown sugar, salt and spices.
Stir ice cream to soften, then fold into pumpkin mixture.
Spoon into graham cracker crust.
Freeze firm.
Garnish with pecans.

title: layered nacho dip
directions: Combine beans and seasoning mix; spread bean mixture evenly in a 12-inch pie pan or foil pizza pan.
Layer remaining ingredients in order listed.
Serve with large corn chips.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat 3 minutes.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool 15 minutes in pan.
Turn out on serving plate.
Glaze with vanilla icing.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Combine potatoes with soup and milk. Mix thoroughly; pour into buttered casserole.
Place chops on top and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: red red chili sauce
directions: Grind together first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar and salt. Simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in vinegar and remaining ingredients. Cook 40 minutes, until thick, stirring often.
Remove gauze bag. Fill five 6 1/2 pint sterilized jars.

title: potato 'n broccoli supreme casserole
directions: Whip
together	potatoes,
cream
cheese, milk, egg and margarine until smooth.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Fold
in
cup	French fried onion.
Spread potato mixture over bottom and up sides of a buttered 8 x 12-inch baking dish to form
shell.
Bake	uncovered at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Arrange
hot
broccoli
spears
in potato shell; sprinkle with cheese and remaining onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes longer. Makes 8 servings.

title: spiced apple squares
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs until blended. Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt mixture gradually. Stir in vanilla, apples and nuts. Spread in 9 x 13-inch oiled baking dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until it pulls from the sides of pan. Spread with Maple Frosting while cake is still warm. May be topped with additional nuts.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Puree stewed tomato juice only, garlic and 2 jalapenos in a blender or processor.
Finely chop the onion, 1 jalapeno, 2 or 3 Tbsp cilantro and 4 to 6 Roma tomatoes.
Roughly chop the stewed tomatoes.
Mix all of these ingredients in a large bowl.
Season with kosher salt, fresh ground pepper and lime juice.

title: appetizers
directions: Layer in order given, in two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly.

title: cheesy chicken chowder
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large saucepan.
Cover and cook 15 minutes until tender.
Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Add flour and stir until smooth. Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat. Stir until thickened and bubbly.
Gradually stir in vegetable mixture, soy sauce, chicken and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted and thoroughly heated.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: crullers
directions: Roll out dough about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut dough in small squares.
Make a cut with knife in center and draw one end of square through this to make a bow.
Fry in deep fat.
Drain on absorbent paper and cool.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after every addition.
Dissolve chocolate in boiling water; cool slightly and add to egg mixture.
Sift flour, salt and soda together.
Add to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk. Mix well and add vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done; check with toothpick or if it springs back when touched.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: broccoli cheese potato topper
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, stir soup, sour cream and mustard. Heat good, stirring occasionally.
Stir in broccoli flowerets. Heat and spoon in baked potatoes.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together.
Drain fruit cocktail good before adding to mixture.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into bowl.
Decorate top with drained maraschino cherries.

title: molasses-nut bread
directions: Combine
egg,
molasses,
sugar,
butter
or
margarine, lemon rind and lemon juice
in
a
large
mixing
bowl, beating well. Combine flour, baking powder,
soda and salt; add to egg mixture alternately with
buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well
after each addition.
Stir in pecans. Spoon batter in a greased and
floured
1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan, and bake at 350°
for
to
minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove loaf from
pan and let cook completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender; take off bone and cut into small pieces.
Melt butter and pour over crumbs.
Put half of crumbs into baking dish, then add chicken.
Mix soup mixture with 2 cans of chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: no sugar raisin cake
directions: Bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes or until done at 350°.
Nuts can be added.

title: black forest cheesecake
directions: Combine
crumbs
and butter.
Put in 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: copper carrots
directions: Place carrots in casserole dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar, salt and
onions
over carrots.
Dot with margarine or butter. Cover tightly and
bake in oven set at 350° for 30 minutes, or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: creole vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add vegetables; season.
Cover. Simmer 30 minutes or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix lettuce, cheese, onion, tomatoes and cooled browned hamburger.
Mix taco seasoning and Miracle Whip together.
Mix with rest of salad.
Just before serving cover salad with broken Doritos chips.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Place chops or roast in large clear plastic bag.
Pour in marinade and close bag tightly. Marinate 2 to 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Remove roast, place on rack in shallow roasting pan. Roast, uncovered, at 325° for 3 hours.
Baste with marinade.
If using chops, bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or cook on charcoal grill 10 minutes each side.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions in a 10 x 14-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare pudding according to package directions and refrigerate 5 to 10 minutes.
Whip cream cheese until smooth.
Slowly add instant pudding and whip until smooth.
Add whipped topping and whip until very well blended. Place pineapple over cooled cake.
Top with cream cheese pudding mixture.
Spread coconut over mixture.
Top with chopped nuts.

title: double chocolate nuggets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, oil and eggs.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. If desired, top each cookie with a pecan half.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until cookie tests done with a toothpick.
Cool on cookie sheet about 1 minute, then remove to rack to finish cooling.
Makes about 4 to 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: dave's opening day trout(servings: 2)
directions: Clean the trout, removing the heads and washing the inner cavity thoroughly.
Mix the salt and pepper with the flour.
Salt and pepper the cavity and dredge the inside and outside in the flour mixture.

title: picante con queso
directions: Heat Velveeta cheese, milk and picante sauce over low heat; stir until sauce is smooth.
Serve with tortilla chips, corn chips or fresh vegetables.

title: shelby's apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using one end of the stick of butter or margarine grease the sides and bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Peel, core and slice the apples and distribute evenly in the pan. Sprinkle the sugar/cinnamon mixture over the apples.

Using your hand, sprinkle the dry cake mix evenly over the entire pan, covering the apples (you should use 1/2 to 3/4 of the cake mix). Using the remaining butter or margarine dot the top of the cake mix.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes until top is browned.

title: butter bean soup
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan over medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Stir in onion and cook for 5 minutes, until tender. Drain off excess fat. Add all cans of vegetables, beans, seasoning, salt and pepper. Stir and reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes, until heated through. Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients together and mix in 1 cup cranberries. Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes.

title: citrus dill sauce-dip
directions: Combine honey, orange peel, dill weed and orange juice.
Stir until well combined.
Cover and chill until serving time.
Serve with fresh vegetables.
Makes 1 cup.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix well and pat into an unbaked pie shell.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with margarine.
Top with pie crust.
Seal well and bake at 350°.
Slice as pie wedges and serve with catsup.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Saute ham, onion and hot pepper sauce in oil over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until onions are soft, but not browned.
Combine black-eyed peas, ham mixture and rice, then heat.
Garnish with thin slices of ham and greens.

title: angel food cake(this recipe is over 50 years old.)
directions: Add cream of tartar to egg whites before beating. Then beat until whites form peaks, but not too dry.
Gradually add sugar, then the flour.
Place the batter in an angel food cake pan.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Increase the temperature to 325° and bake for 15 additional minutes.

title: rice krispies treats(kellogg's original)
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat. Add Kellogg's Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated. Using buttered spatula or waxed paper, press mixture evenly into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into squares when cool.
Makes 24 treats (2 x 2-inch).

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add vinegar; mix well.
(I use old fashioned eggbeater.)
Beat in eggs.
Add oil.
Mix well.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cube potatoes, cooked until tender. Drain.
Make cheese sauce as follows:
Melt butter or margarine in saucepan; add flour and stir to a smooth paste.
Add scalded milk, slat, pepper and cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Pour over cooked potatoes and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This can also be made in an electric skillet.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss together with the salad dressing.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: For syrup, cook over medium heat approximately 5 minutes. Test the thickness of the syrup by putting small amount of the mixture in cold water to form soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Stir the nuts until well coated.
Lay out on aluminum foil to set.
Cool.
Store in an attractive container, these make a wonderful hostess gift during the holidays.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Combine orange slice candy, dates, walnuts and coconut.
Add 1/2 cup flour mixture to them.
Blend with spoon until light the butter, sugar and eggs.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine soda and buttermilk and add alternately with flour mixture to candy mix.

Bake in large tube pan or 3 loaf pans, greased and floured, for 1 hour and 45 minutes in 300° oven. Combine orange juice and powdered sugar and pour over hot cake. Let cool and store in refrigerator overnight before removing from pan.

title: pork chops with mushroom gravy
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet, over medium-low heat.
Add pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown chops on both sides. Transfer chops to casserole dish or around 13 x 9-inch pan for oven.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour prepared gravy over chops and sprinkle mushrooms over chops.
Put in oven for about 30 minutes.

title: seasoned pumpkin seed
directions: Remove membrane from seed; rinse and pat dry.
Place seeds in an 8-inch square pan; add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat. Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring occasionally.
Yield:
3/4 cup.

title: dixie's orange bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is like corn meal.
Squeeze orange for juice.
Shred the orange rind; combine with the orange juice, egg and sugar. Stir liquid mixture into dry ingredients just enough to moisten. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: ham pat
directions: In food processor, blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, onion, mustard, parsley and tabasco. Add finely chopped ham and mix well. Refrigerate until enough to shape into a mound. Serve with crackers.

title: virginia sally lunn bread
directions: After milk cools slightly, add all but 1 cup flour; beat for 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour.
Let rise 1 hour.
Beat with wooden spoon; pour into angel food pan greased.
Let rise 1 hour or until 1-inch from top of pan.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes until golden brown.

title: sausage lentil soup(yield: 6 servings)
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown and crumble the sausage.
Drain fat. Add then next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until the lentils and vegetables are tender.
Stir in the mustard. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix sugar, chips and milk in a bowl. Mix in peanut butter. Mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls.

title: molasses pie
directions: Mix and pour in uncooked crust; bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Drain in large saucepan.
Add cream of mushroom soup and 3 cups of water to beef and onion mixture.
Add vegetables, salt and pepper and cook slowly for 45 minutes or until vegetables are done.

title: 5 hour "no peek" beef stew
directions: Cover and place in oven and cook for at least 5 hours at 250°. Do not remove lid during cooking time.
"No peek." Can also be cooked in crock-pot on high for 4 1/2 hours, but better in the oven.

title: saucy chicken
directions: Pour 1/2 cup broth in bowl.
Place flour mixture on plate. Dip each chicken breast in broth, then flour.
Use non-stick cooking spray in fry pan.
Fry in skillet on medium heat until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add remaining flour, cook until browned.
Slowly stir in broth until slightly thickened.
Add tomatoes and scallions.
Return chicken to mixture.
Simmer chicken until hot.
Each serving 182 calories.

title: cheesy pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in bottom of a casserole dish and cover with sliced potatoes, Cheddar cheese soup and onion soup.
Cover and bake at 425° for 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until brown.

title: chocolate ambrosia dessert
directions: Melt chocolate with milk over low heat, stirring until smooth. Add cream cheese; stir until melted. Stir in vanilla. Gradually add sugar, mixing until well blended. Combine oranges and coconut; toss lightly. For each serving, cover one cake slice with 1/4 c. orange mixture; top with 2 Tbsp. sauce. To reheat, spoon sauce into saucepan; stir over low heat until thoroughly heated. Makes 6 servings.

title: 3 cheese vegetable lasagna
directions: In covered 10-inch skillet, combine water, broccoli, carrots, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and drain after 10 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine soup, Parmesan, Ricotta and Mozzarella cheeses.
Stir in vegetable mixture.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil; remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Butter a 12 x 17-inch cookie sheet and press the mixture onto the cookie sheet. Melt chips together either in microwave or double boiler and spread onto bars.

title: skillet pork stew
directions: Spray 12 inch nonstick skillet with nonstick cooking spray; heat over medium high heat. Cook pork in skillet 3 to 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until light brown. Stir in gravy, ketchup and potatoes. Heat to boiling; reduce heat to medium low. Cover and cook 10 minutes. Stir in beans (or other vegetable you prefer). Cover and cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Line casserole dish with chilies face down.
Cook meat then put on top of that.
Next mix flour, milk, and eggs together and pour on top of cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 min. then take out and pour picante on top and bake for 15 min. more.
This can be put together the night before.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sear meat in oil, stir in onion, salt, pepper, Worcestershire, tomato paste and beef bouillon.
Cover and cook about 30 minutes or until tender.
Then add mushrooms, stir in flour and cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add sour cream and wine and heat thoroughly but do not boil.
Serve on noodles in in crepes.

title: blueberry tarte
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put into pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350 degrees.
Let cool completely.

title: sorghum milkshake
directions: Blend sorghum and milk thoroughly in a blender to froth. Serve very cold over cracked ice or with a scoop of ice cream.

title: farm cookies
directions: Cream together white sugar, brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla, salt and soda.
Add flour, blending well.
Add oatmeal, chips and coconut.

title: chicken and dried beef casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with chipped beef.
Place chicken breasts atop beef.
Mix chicken soup, mushroom soup, mushrooms and sour cream.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake until done at 350° or at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, covered.

title: quick and delicious shrimp casserole
directions: Place shrimp in a 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
In a skillet, saute mushrooms in 3 teaspoons of butter or margarine.
Transfer to a bowl.
Toss with flour.
Stir in sour cream, remaining butter and soy sauce.
Pour over shrimp. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika. Bake at 400° for 2 to 3 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese and Cool Whip until smooth. Add marshmallow cream and mix in pudding.
Whip it all together.
Chill.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: yum yum cake
directions: Cake should be layered as follows:

title: peanut butter pinwheels
directions: To the potatoes, add enough confectioners sugar to make easily handled fondant; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Turn half of mixture onto board that has been lightly dusted with powdered sugar.
Roll into a rectangle 1/4-inch thick.
Spread with half of peanut butter, then roll short side jellyroll fashion.
Repeat with rest of fondant.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Cut into 1/4-inch thick slices.

title: diabetic peaches
directions: Select good peaches without green or rot.
Scald and peel peaches.
Slice thin.
Pour pineapple juice (unsweetened) over peaches and let set a few minutes.
Put in boxes and freeze.
They are out of this world and no sugar.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on cake mix.
Stir in sour cream and coconut and bake as directed on cake mix package.
Cool 10 minutes and poke holes in cake with the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour the whole can of creme of coconut over cake and into holes. Refrigerate.
Before serving, frost with Cool Whip and sprinkle with more coconut, is desired.
Keep chilled.

title: slush
directions: Bring to boil 7 cups water and 4 tea bags to light flavor. Mix tea and water with orange juice, lemonade, ginger ale and vodka.
Mix well and freeze.
Scoop 4 ounces in 8 ounce glass and fill rest of glass with 7-Up.
Enjoy on hot day or any day.

title: marsha's baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat with pepper and onion in skillet.
Mix in all other ingredients and serve.

title: broccoli-lima bean casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and lima beans according to package.
Drain. To cooked broccoli/lima beans, add sour cream, mushroom soup, water chestnuts and onion soup mix.
Pour in a casserole dish. Cover top with Rice Krispies.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alaska salmon pot pies
directions: Drain salmon; set aside.
Saute onion; add mushrooms in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat for 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, milk, tarragon and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Whisk in instant potatoes, then stir in corn, peas and salmon. Cook over medium heat until heated through.
Spoon into baking dish.
Cover with pastry.
Seal edges of dough against side of dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until crust is golden brown.
May also be prepared in individual ovenproof serving dishes.

title: dick's taco casserole
directions: Cook and drain meat; add seasoning mix, chile peppers and tomatoes.
Layer bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with the beans.
Then add beef mixture; then sour cream and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Top with crushed potato chips or Doritos.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over chips.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes more until cheese melts.
Serve with shredded lettuce and picante sauce.

title: foil-wrapped sandwiches
directions: Put all ingredients, except buns, through a meat grinder. Spread on hot dog buns. Wrap each in aluminum foil.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: anniversary salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water in large flat Pyrex dish.
Stir in drained fruit (save juice).
Sprinkle marshmallows over top and refrigerate.
Mix sugar, flour and beaten egg.
Add 1 cup of juice and butter.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it bubbles.
Chill until cold.
Chill bowl; beat whipping cream and fold into custard; spread over jello mixture.
Grate 1/2 cup sharp cheese on top.

title: honey 'n' spice glazed chicken
directions: Combine 57 sauce and honey.
Brush chicken with melted butter, then 57 sauce and honey mixture.
Broil until chicken is cooked, turning and brushing with 57 mixture frequently.
Makes 5 servings.

title: marshmallow caramel balls
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt together the caramels, butter and condensed milk until smooth.
May need to add up to 1/4 cup more evaporated milk to make smooth.
With metal fork, dip large marshmallows into sauce, then roll in Rice Krispies.
(May add nuts and coconut to Rice Krispies.)

title: sunshine salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; cool and serve.

title: chocolate chip whip
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix margarine (melted), flour and crushed nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Glaze:
In a large saucepan, place sliced strawberries, condensed milk, shredded coconut, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 cup milk.
On low heat, mix and stir after adding milk as desired.
Do not overdo milk!
Simmer and mix until glaze turns pink, then cool.

title: crispy bars
directions: Melt chocolate chips, butterscotch chips and butter until smooth.
Stir in cornflakes.
Put in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Let stand 10 minutes and cut in bars.

title: holiday punch
directions: In an 8-quart punch bowl, combine Twister and ginger ale.
Add small scoops of sherbet.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Makes 24 (8 ounce) servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown rice in margarine; pour in casserole dish.
Mix all 3 soups in saucepan; rinse cans with small amount of water.
Heat until mixed well.
Pour over rice and stir up.
Place choice parts of fryer on top of casserole with skin side up.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: easy cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in cake mix (dry), cherry pie filling and oil until blended.
Spread in pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. (Surface of cake will be bumpy.) Cool completely.

title: queso dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in slow cooker, crock-pot or fondue pot until hot.
Serve with tostados.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add rice and stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add green onions and soy sauce.
Push rice aside.
Add eggs.
Stir the rice into the eggs.
Add meat and heat thoroughly.
Mix well.

title: mama's marshmallow brownies
directions: Cream together sugar, margarine and eggs, adding eggs slowly. Sift together flour and cocoa and add to mixture.
Stir in pecans or walnuts.
Spread ingredients into greased pan, 11 x 14-inch. Bake at 325° to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and beat fast for 8 minutes. Combine sugar, cinnamon and pecans.
Pour 1/2 of dough mixture into a greased and floured bundt pan; sprinkle on 1/2 of sugar mixture.
Add rest of dough and then remaining sugar mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or for the time instructed on cake mix box.

title: peanut butter cup dessert
directions: Take first 3 ingredients, mix together.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.
Take next 4 ingredients, mix together.
Spread on crust.
Take remaining 3 ingredients, mix together.
Spread onto peanut butter mixture. Top with Cool Whip.
Grate a chocolate candy bar.
Sprinkle on top.
Refrigerate.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix well.
Use 1 or 2 tsp in a cup of hot or cold water.

title: impossible chicken pie
directions: In deep saucepan, place chicken. Add water and 1 teaspoon of salt.

Cover and simmer about 45 minutes or until fork can be inserted in chicken with ease. Cool. Separate meat from bones. Discard bones and skin. Cut chicken in bite size pieces and place in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of the Mozzarella cheese, tomato paste, oregano and basil. Stir to mix and set aside.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Fold together and pour into 2 graham cracker crusts.
Top with Cool Whip or pecans.
Chill.

title: cookie cake
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Boil butter, water and cocoa and pour over flour mixture.
Add buttermilk, soda, vanilla and eggs.
Bake at 400° on a cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Ice while warm.

title: black bean enchilada
