directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Spoon 2/3 cup enchilada sauce in the bottom of ungreased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Heat oil in skillet. Add onion, pepper and garlic. Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until onions are tender. Combine onion mixture and beans. Spoon about 2 tablespoonfuls bean mix into each tortilla. Top with 2 tablespoonfuls of cheese and roll up. Place, seam side down, in enchilada sauce. Spoon remaining sauce over the top. Top with cheese. Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: christmas aroma
directions: Simmer.
Add water as needed.
"Hide" in oven until needed.

title: barbecue chicken wings
directions: Layer in casserole onion and celery.
Season with salt.
Layer apple.
Pour a little barbecue sauce over.
Add a layer of chicken wings, disjointed.
Season with salt.
Add more barbecue sauce to cover wings.
Bake at 400° for 55 minutes (that temperature is for a trailer oven).

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Divide cake mix in half. Mix half of cake with 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 cup of butter (1 stick).
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Blend sugar and eggs with shortening.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Add mashed bananas and lemon juice; mix.
Fold in chopped nuts.

title: braised sirloin tips over rice
directions: Melt shortening, brown meat on all sides in skillet.
Stir in consomme, wine, soy sauce, garlic and onion salt.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
Blend cornstarch and water.
Stir gradually into meat mixture.
Stirring until thickened.
Serve over rice.
If you need to reduce salt, use less soy sauce (1/2) and place onion salt with onion flakes or minced onion.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gelatin dessert (sugar-free)
directions: Add 1/4 cup boiling water to Jell-O to dissolve.
Congeal 1/2 of mixture with exception of sour cream.
Spread sour cream with rubber spatula on 1/2 of congealed mixture.
Then cover with remaining mixture.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg yolks.
Add flour and rind or juice of lemon.
Add milk.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add to mixture.
Pour in crust.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, 1/2 carton thawed Cool Whip, pudding mix and spice.
Blend well one to two minutes.
Put into crust and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Quick-chill in freezer for ten minutes. Dust top with additional spice.

title: tangy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Use as a basting sauce when grilling chicken, pork or beef.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine in large saucepan the water, oil and cocoa.
Mix over heat until boiling.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add eggs and beat with spoon or hand mixer.
Add flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until pick comes out clean.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Saute onion and red pepper in butter until tender.
Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Add cheeses to hot noodles; stir until cheese melts.
Stir in onion mixture, peas, mushrooms and pepper.
Spoon into a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes. Yield:
8 servings.

title: livery stable strawberry bread
directions: Place berries in medium bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Let stand until thawed and then slice.
Preheat to 350°.
Grease 2 (9 x 15-inch) loaf pans.
Combine flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and baking soda.
Mix well in large bowl.
Add oil and eggs to berries.
Add flour mixture; stir in pecans.
Blend until ingredients are moistened.
Divide batter between 2 pans.
Bake until toothpick comes clean in center, 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out on rack and cool again.

title: canned green tomatoes
directions: Slice green tomatoes thick.
Put in pint jars with salt, fill with water.
Put lids on jars; put in deep pot or canner, cover with water and cook 15 minutes.

title: imperial cookies
directions: Mix well and set overnight in refrigerator. Next day, divide dough into 4 sections.
Handle lightly and put into rolls. Wrap in wax paper. Store in refrigerator overnight.
Slice thin and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly brown.

title: microwave mochi
directions: Wash the rice.
Let soak overnight. Before you start the mochi, make quarter size balls of tsubushi an.
Have these ready before you form the mochi and life will be so much easier.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix first three ingredients together; form into balls the size of a buckeye (one-inch).
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate star peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Beat well the next 2 ingredients and add sugars, vanilla, egg and milk.
Then add sifted dry ingredients.
Shape into balls (walnut-size) and roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Remove and press chocolate stars or Hershey's Kisses into center of cookies.
Bake again for 2 to 5 minutes. Makes 3 to 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Place apples in large bowl; sprinkle sugar over apples and let stand.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to apples.
Add eggs, oil and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add walnuts.
Pour mixture into greased pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: delicious pecans
directions: Combine egg whites and vanilla. Add brown sugar; mix well. Fold in pecan halves. Using a fork, remove individual pecans from mixture and place on a greased baking sheet. Bake for 20 minutes at 200°. Cool completely before storing in an airtight container.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Drain. Melt butter in a saucepan and blend in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually stir in the milk and cook over low heat until thickened. Stir often.
Add the hot diced potatoes to the sauce.
Serves 4.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt margarine and add cocoa; simmer.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Simmer for 7 to 8 minutes.
Add this mixture to powdered sugar.
Beat until cool.
Spread on cake.

title: broccoli salad with feta cheese *
directions: Cut broccoli into small pieces.
Mash garlic with salt; mix in vinegar and beat in olive oil.
Pour over broccoli.
Add radishes, olives and pignoli nuts and marinate for about 5 hours.
Just before serving, add tomatoes and Feta cheese.

title: green salad
directions: Mix ingredients (dissolve Jell-O, marshmallows and cream cheese with the 1 1/2 cups boiling water).
Add pineapple, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix well.
Cool and chill.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions.
Blend Dream Whip into chilled Jell-O mixture.
Congeal and serve.

title: potato lefse
directions: Steam the potatoes.
Do not boil them.
Cook and rice potatoes. Measure the potatoes and add butter.
Let cool.
After mixture is room temperature, mix in flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Mix it up and put flour on a board.
Take mixture and roll into a snake on floured board.
Cut into 16 pieces.
Flour the board each time and roll out thin.
Bake on hot lefse grill or griddle.
Bake a minute or two, and then turn with lefse stick.
Turn when bubbles and brown spots appear.
Fold each lefse in half or quarters.
Cool between towels.
Put in plastic storage bags immediately and freeze.

title: good chicken
directions: Mix diet cola and catsup.
Place chicken in electric skillet. Pour diet cola and catsup over chicken.
Add bell pepper, onions and mushrooms.
Cook at 350°, covered, until done.
The cola/catsup mixture will thicken as it cooks.
Serve with noodles or rice.
Low calorie and good.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt to beaten egg yolks and cook over boiling water until custard consistency.
Pour cold water in bowl and sprinkle gelatine on top of water.
Add to hot custard and stir until dissolved.
Add grated lemon rind.
When mixture begins to thicken, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites to which the other half cup of sugar has been added.
Fill baked pie shell or graham cracker crust and chill.
Just before serving, spread over pie thin layer of whipped cream.

title: "yum-yum" squares
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg into stiff mixture.
Press into bottom of 13 x 15 x 2-inch pan.
Blend rest of ingredients together.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cool before cutting into squares.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and oil.
Save some for topping.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, egg and lemon juice.
Spread over baked cake mixture.
Sprinkle with saved cake mixture.
Bake 15 minutes more at 350°.

title: sweet 'n sour delight
directions: Cut meat into 1/2-inch pieces. Brown in oil. Reduce heat to low.
Add onion and garlic. Cover.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add carrots and bell pepper.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion on pie shell.
Beat eggs slightly.
Beat in remaining salt, pepper and paprika.
Pour cream into egg mixture and pour all into pie shell.
Bake, uncovered, in a 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Bake uncovered until knife comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: old fashioned yeast rolls
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add cup of hot water; set aside.
Dissolve yeast and 1 tablespoon of sugar in the warm water; add to the creamed mixture when cooled.
Add the eggs and the flour, mixing well with bread hook on mixer or big spoon. The dough will look elastic and smooth.
Scrape sides of bowl. Cover with Saran Wrap, then cover with a dish towel.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Push your finger in it; if it comes out clean, stir with a spoon.
Refrigerate until ready to make out into bread of choice (loaf, Parker House rolls, etc.).
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 4 to 6 dozen rolls.

title: cinnamon rolls(cake mix way)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine cake mix and flour; stir in yeast and knead about 8 minutes.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise until double.
On floured board, roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts or raisins.
(I spread some butter on dough first.)
Roll as for jelly roll and cut in 1/2-inch slices.
Cover and let rise.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stardust salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Add cold water, bananas, crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until congealed.
Cook until thick the sugar, egg, flour and pineapple juice.
Cool. Spread cooled mixture over gelatin.
Mix Cool Whip with cream cheese and beat until light.
Spread over second layer and sprinkle sharp cheese over top.

title: spicy italian roast
directions: Season roast with garlic salt.
Place in crock-pot.
Add mushrooms and chopped onion.
Combine seasoning mix and tomato sauce.
Pour over all.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or on high 4 to 6 hours in crock-pot.

title: apple nut coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch square cake pan.
Beat egg and milk in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Pour your favorite caramel topping over warm cake.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Make cake following directions on package.
Pour into oblong baking dish, 14 x 9-inches.
Bake according to directions.
When cake is done, but still hot, prick the cake all over with a fork. Pour condensed milk slowly to fill holes made with fork.
After the milk has soaked into the cake, spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with frozen coconut and refrigerate.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork chops by tony
directions: Brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon oil and soy sauce.
Add listed ingredients and simmer over low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter balls(buckeyes)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients thoroughly (with hands).
Refrigerate for awhile.

title: rice pudding
directions: *For thicker pudding you may use one quart regular and one quart half and half.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
In saucepan, combine soups and Ro-Tel.
Crunch up bag of Doritos and layer in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch cake pan.
Put deboned chicken on top of Doritos.
Layer soup mix on top of chicken and top off with shredded cheese.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of butter until smooth.
Add next three ingredients and mix.
Separate crescent dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press to seal.
Then cut in half.

title: microwave krispie bars
directions: Combine coating and peanut butter in a 2-quart bowl and microwave on High for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, until coating is melted; stir twice.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Press into lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans and relish.
Dice onion and celery.
One hour before serving time, toss all ingredients together with mayonnaise.
Serve on bed of lettuce.

title: bing cherry mold
directions: Heat 1 cup cherry juice and the Port wine.
Pour remaining cherry juice over plain gelatin.
Put both gelatins together and dissolve in hot cherry juice and Port wine.
Stir and mix together.
Add cherries, which have been cut in half.
Pour into ring mold.
Serve with cream cheese that has been softened with a bit of cream.

title: pineapple and ice cream congealed salad
directions: Add water to jello; stir.
Add ice cream and pineapple juice; let set in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Next, add crushed pineapple and bananas.
Return to refrigerator to congeal.

title: sherried apple pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in butter. Put apples and onions over browned chops.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour on top.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chowder
directions: *Use 2 cans of College Inn brand chicken broth.

title: delicious lasagne
directions: Brown the ground beef in skillet; drain the grease.
Add Ragu spaghetti sauce, chopped mushrooms and chopped onion.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook the lasagne noodles in boiling water according to the directions on the box.
Use a 13 x 9-inch pan. Cover the bottom of the pan with spaghetti sauce.
Put in a layer of noodles, then a layer of cottage cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses over, then layer of noodles, layer of sauce, until you get to the top.
Top with layer of noodles, sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peppered pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with Worcestershire sauce.
Press pepper and thyme into chops.
Arrange in a baking dish.
Cover with wax paper. Turning chops over midway through cooking, microwave on Medium speed for 14 to 16 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, milk and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread on bottom of pie crust.

title: sugarless apple cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine dates, apples, raisins and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Stir into apple mixture and mix well.
Combine eggs and sweetener.
Add to batter.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: creamy baked potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix thoroughly. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with foil.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil and brown during last 10 minutes or baking.

title: angel food pineapple cake(serves 20)
directions: Tear or cut angel food cake into small bite-size pieces and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/2 of the undrained pineapple, Cool Whip and cherries.
Repeat layering, ending with Cool Whip on top.

title: seafood dip
directions: Add all ingredients, except olives; mix well.
Chill.
Garnish with olives when serving.
Yield: 2 cups dip.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat.
Add buttermilk and mix.
Add baking soda and vinegar mixture and mix.
Batter is thick and smooth.

title: ensalada de noche buena(christmas eve salad)
directions: Remove crown of fresh pineapple; peel and remove eyes. Quarter and remove core.
Cut pineapple into chunks (or drain canned pineapple).
Peel oranges; section over a bowl to catch juice.
Peel and slice bananas.
Core and slice apple.
Toss apple and banana with orange sections and orange juice.
Drain fruits.
Arrange with pineapple chunks, sliced beets, jicama and sugar cane on large lettuce lined platter.
Sprinkle with peanuts and pomegranate seeds.
Thin mayonnaise or salad dressing with a little milk to make drizzling consistency.
Pass with salad. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple dessert
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, beaten, and flavorings. Stir.
Add dry ingredients and water.
Stir until mixed.
Add apples and pecans.
Mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch loaf pan about 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with Butter Rum Sauce.

title: macaroons
directions: Add all of the ingredients to the beaten egg whites until well blended.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10-inch pie pan.
Heat 1 inch salted water to boiling.
Add broccoli.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Cook until tender (5 minutes).
Drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese.
Spread in pie pan.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high speed.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: spanish coffee cake
directions: Mix
first
six
ingredients
well.
Reserve 1/2 cup of this mixture
for
topping.
Now add to the first mixture the buttermilk,
soda, baking powder and egg.
Mix batter well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread over batter 1/2 cup of reserved
topping
to
which 1/2 cup of chopped nuts may be added. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cake travels well.

title: hello dolly bars
directions: Melt butter on low heat and add cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of dish.
Layer chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all these ingredients.
Bake 1/2 hour at 325°.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients and keep in an airtight container.
Use 2 to 3 heaping teaspoons for each mug of hot water.

title: baked onion potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1 to 2-inch squares.
Mix onion soup mix and oil in a plastic bag and add potatoes. Shake until coated.
Place in cake pan. Bake at 450°, stirring occasionally, for 40 minutes.

title: surprisingly simple chicken cacciatore
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper, then coat with flour and sprinkle with paprika.
In large skillet, heat 3 tablespoons oil. Brown chicken and garlic; drain.
Stir in Classico pasta sauce. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes, adding green and red bell peppers last 5 minutes.
Prepare Creamette thin spaghetti according to package directions; drain and toss with remaining 1 tablespoon oil.
Arrange on warm serving platter.
Top with hot chicken sauce and cheese.
Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: company ham bake
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Place in shallow 2 quart baking dish.
Top with ham.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and vinegar.
Pour over ham mixture.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until top is browned.
Serves 6.

title: chicken corn soup
directions: In large kettle, cook carrots, celery and onions in chicken stock.
When vegetables are tender, add parsley, corn and chicken. Cook for 10 minutes.
Add macaroni, heat to serving temperature. Yield 4 to 6 servings.

title: macaroni-tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water according to package directions. Rinse in hot water and drain.
Meanwhile, melt butter in skillet. Add onion; cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Slowly add and stir in the milk.
Cook and stir constantly until mixture is smooth and thickened.
Add cheese, stir mixture until cheese melts. Stir in tomatoes and tuna; heat thoroughly.
Turn drained macaroni into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour the hot macaroni into a 2-quart casserole.
Pour the hot tomato-tuna over the macaroni and toss to mix well.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over the top.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes or until mixture is thoroughly heated and crumbs are brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan log
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into small logs.
Freeze.
Mix the next 4 ingredients.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Dip the frozen logs into the syrup.
Roll in nuts.
Place on waxed paper to cool.
May freeze.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs one at a time.
Melt butter.
Stir in buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla flavor.
Then bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes until brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat until almost done.
Add bell pepper and onion and continue to cook 5 additional minutes or until meat is completely done.
To this mixture, add tomato sauce, oregano, garlic powder, bay leaves and mushrooms.
Simmer on low heat for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over spaghetti or your choice of pasta.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Turn dough onto floured countertop.
Shape dough into a ball and cut in half and roll in the shape of a cookie roll.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
Slice and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Add oil to sugar in mixing bowl and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add pumpkin to this mixture.
Add all other ingredients and mix.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: baked apple wrap
directions: Microwave apple slices for 3 minutes. Separate crescent rolls and wrap each slice of apple with dough and place in a deep dish. Mix sugar and brown sugar. Sprinkle over apples and dough. Melt butter and pour over mixture, then pour Sprite or 7-Up over the mixture. Sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350° until dough rises and is brown. Serve hot or cold.

title: pickled beets
directions: Marinate beets in this dressing mixture overnight or several days if kept cold.

title: lemon macadamia nut delight
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add flour and 1/2 cup nuts. Press into the bottom of a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes until light brown.
Prepare lemon pudding according to package directions.
Cool and spread on cooled crust.
Prepare whipped topping according to package directions.
Spread on cooled pudding and sprinkle 1/4 cup nut bits on top.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl combine first five ingredients until well blended.
Stir in pecans, pour in pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: peanut butter ice cream pie
directions: Place ice cream in mixing bowl.
Stir just to soften.
Fold in 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Carefully fold in 4 ounce Cool Whip. Quickly spoon into graham cracker crust; sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs and freeze until firm.

title: cheese strata
directions: Cut 12 doughnuts and holes from bread with doughnut cutter; set aside.
Arrange remaining bread over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer cheese, broccoli and ham over top.
Arrange bread cut-outs over top.
Combine next 5 ingredients in bowl; pour over bread.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook chicken broth, broccoli and onion.
Bring to a boil; simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.
Make a paste of butter and flour.
Gradually add to mixture.
Stirring constantly, add remaining ingredients.
Cook until hot.
Do not boil.

title: bread dumplings with bacon
directions: Cut bread into very fine slices; pour boiling milk over them. Soak 1 hour.
Fry bacon and onion together; leave to cool.
Stir into the bread and milk; add cornstarch.
Knead mixture until it forms a smooth, compact ball.
Cool, then stir in eggs one at a time.
Add parsley; stir in baking powder and season with salt.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put raw rice in bottom of greased dish; add soup and water to rice and mix well.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces with skin side up.
Set chicken on rice mixture (as much as you want).
Bake, uncovered at 350° to 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: delicious italian strufoli
directions: Mix together.
Now add water, a little at a time (just enough to hold together).
If too sticky, add a little more flour.
Roll dough into a ball.
Now cut off small pieces; roll the small pieces into a long roll.
Cut into 1/2-inch pieces; fry in hot fat until golden brown.
Put into a deep bowl; pour warm honey or maple syrup until well coated.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook pineapple, flour and sugar until thick.
Remove from heat and add margarine.
Stir until the margarine melts.
Cool.
Peel and slice apples in mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: leek potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in water just to cover with leeks.
Add salt. When done, add milk for more broth as needed.
Add butter or margarine and bacon bits.
I use potato masher to mash potatoes some so it's thicker.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Melt butter.
Add cream and sugar.
Cook until a little past soft ball stage.
(Don't cook too fast, it scorches easily.)
Turn off and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Put thin layer of crumbs in bottom of baking dish.
Alternate layers of oysters and crumbs, sprinkling each layer with seasoning.
(No more than 2 layers of oysters.)
Pour cream of mushroom soup over dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: nine bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in a large pot; cover with water and add salt.
Bring to a boil, remove from heat, cover tightly and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain; cover with the 2 quarts of water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, simmer 30 minutes.
Add onion, meat or bone, salt and pepper to taste and continue to simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add tomatoes and chili powder during the last 30 minutes of cooking time.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.
Great served with corn bread.

title: children's play bubbles
directions: Mix together.
Store in empty milk jug containers.

title: sir thomas spain
directions: Beat the eggs with a fork in a small deep bowl.
Add onions and green chilies or peppers.
Heat butter in frying pan over medium high heat until bubbling.
Pour in egg mixture.
Stir gently until cooked.
Spoon on bottom muffin halves.
Top with remaining muffin halves and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with bread or vegetables.

title: cider wassail
directions: *Put ingredients in cheesecloth and boil in water for 10 minutes.

title: party popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pecan halves and slivered almonds in a single layer in a roasting pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes, stirring often, until nuts are lightly browned.
Remove from oven; add popped corn and salt.
Melt butter and brown sugar in a small saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in popped corn nut mixture until well coated.
Bake 10 minutes longer, stirring only once until golden brown.
Remove from oven and cool in pan.
Store in tightly covered containers.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 7 ingredients.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add well-beaten egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° until a crack develops on top and the cake tester comes out clean.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon; add onions and cook until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
(Do not drain before adding remaining ingredients.)
Mix and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes, uncovered.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix all together; put in greased tube pan at 300° for 2 hours.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Prepare pastry.
Bake 5 minutes.
If using frozen pie crusts, follow directions for crust to be filled.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, salt, pepper, carrot, sour cream, soup and onion. Melt margarine and mix with stuffing.
Put 1/2 of stuffing on the bottom of casserole.
Add squash mixture and top with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6. This freezes well, also.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix with buttermilk, flour and soda.
Add oil and sugar.
Mix until flour is dissolved.
Roll and cut into biscuits.
May be cooked at once or let rise for a few minutes.
(This may also be kept in refrigerator for several days in covered bowl.)
Preheat oven to 375° to 400° and cook until brown (about 12 to 16 minutes).

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together butter, flour and pecans.
Spread in a 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and cool.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: Mix and pour in a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir in all ingredients except potato chips.
Put in casserole dish. If cheesier flavor is desired, layer mixture with sliced American cheese in the middle and more on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Add crushed potato chips on top and bake for an additional 10 minutes.

title: early breakfast strata
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage; drain.
In large bowl, beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover.
Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Stir in sour cream.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Brush top of pie crust with maple syrup.
Sprinkle some pecans on top if desired.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Saute onions, celery and green peppers in butter.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until melted. Combine rice, broccoli and soup mixture.
Mix well.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch spectacular
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans for pie crust.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter
in a 9 x 12-inch pan and sprinkle crackers on top.
On
top of crumbs, sprinkle in this order:
chocolate chips, coconut
and drizzle condensed milk over this.
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
Cut in squares or bars.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix Cheez Whiz and cream of mushroom soup together, then add all other ingredients to the cheese and soup mixture.
Put in medium casserole and heat thoroughly.

title: janice's favorite pie
directions: Mix by hand, lemonade, milk, topping and enough food coloring for desired shade of pink.
Pour into either a 9-inch baked pie shell or a graham cracker crust and chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Gradually add Marshmallow Creme to softened cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add orange rind and ginger and whip until fluffy.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put the following in a jar: sugar, salad or vegetable oil and vinegar.
Shake well and pour over salad.
Let stand for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Drain and serve.

title: sausage and corn casserole
directions: Brown sliced sausage in large pan.
Add onion and bell peppers. Saute until tender.
Add corn, milk and crushed saltines to thicken.
You can cook this on top the stove, scraping and stirring occasionally for 1 hour.
Or bake in the oven at 325°.
If you use pimentos instead of red bell peppers, stir them in during the last 1/2 hour of cooking time.
Freezes well.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a pie plate.
Cover with chili. Top with Mozzarella cheese.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
On top, put cubed bread.
Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix beef, sausage, rice and onions.
Mix well.
Roll in balls and wrap in cabbage leaves.

title: grandma's white cake
directions: Note:
If your cake flour has the baking powder and salt already in it, then omit these 2 ingredients.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and spices; stir in eggs and beat.
Add milk, pumpkin and cream or milk.
Pour into pie crust shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
When tester comes out nearly clean, pie is done.
Cool and top with cream and 1/2 cup toasted coconut.
Topping is optional.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse and pick over lentils; soak overnight.
Drain well.
In a large pot, saute bacon until golden.
Add carrots and onions, and saute until onions are golden.
Add celery, water, lentils, seasonings, potato and ham bone.
Simmer covered for 4 hours until vegetables are tender and broth is thick.
Remove ham bone and return bits of meat to soup, discarding bone.
Soup keeps for a long time in refrigerator and freezes well.

title: made rights
directions: Finely chop onion.
Brown onion and ground chuck.
Season to taste.
Serve on a sandwich bun with mustard and ketchup as desired.

title: different bread pudding
directions: Place crumbs in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix other ingredients together and pour over crumbs.
Bake at 350° until pudding is set and medium brown on top.
(One-half cup peanut butter
or 1/4 cup cocoa may be substituted instead of coconut.)

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mash and reheat beans.
Beat eggs and blend with beans.
Add remainder of ingredients and and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Then turn back heat to 300° and bake 10 minutes.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Combine cake mix and baking soda. Add eggs, buttermilk, food coloring and vanilla. Blend on low until moistened. Beat on high for 2 minutes. Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool before icing.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool thoroughly.
Break 1/2 cake into small pieces and put in bottom of punch bowl.
Make 1 box of pudding according to recipe and pour over cake.
Spread 1 can of cherry pie filling over this, then spread 1 can of crushed pineapple over cherry filling.
Spread 1/2 Cool Whip over this. Repeat the entire process.
Sprinkle the nuts over the last layer of Cool Whip.
Chill.
Will feed 25 to 30 people.

title: kathy's french bread
directions: Saute
mushrooms,
salt,
mustard,
lemon juice, garlic salt, onion,
poppy
seed and margarine together.
Cut X's in loaf of bread; don't cut through.
Cut Swiss cheese in strips and
stick between
bread X's.
Pour sauteed mixture over and between bread. Wrap
in
tin
foil.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.

title: trout in foil
directions: Clean fish; sprinkle cavity with salt and pepper.
For each fish, fashion double thickness aluminum foil.
Place lettuce leaf, fish, 1 slice bacon and 2 slices lemon.
Wrap and seal the foil. Cook on medium coals about 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix as you would corn bread. Pour into a preheated, well oiled, heavy Bundt pan or large, heavy skillet. Preheat utensil to 425° before oiling and bake about 45 minutes or until well browned. (Heat pan before oiling.)

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine and pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. In separate bowl, combine cream-style corn, whole kernel corn, milk, eggs, flour and sugar; mix well.
Pour corn mixture on top of melted butter in casserole dish; sprinkle entire top with crushed cracker crumbs (12 to 15 crackers).
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: roasted potato fans
directions: Being careful not to cut all the way through, make slices every 1/4 inch in potatoes.
Pour butter into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange potatoes, cut side up, in dish.
Brush with butter; sprinkle with salt, basil, marjoram and pepper.
Bake at 400°, basting occasionally, for 1 hour, or until potatoes are brown.

title: beef sausage corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Place sausage in large skillet and fry until browned on all sides.
Remove sausage from skillet and cut each in quarters.
Place corn meal mix in large mixing bowl, stirring with wooden spoon.
Add egg, milk and beef drippings from skillet.
Stir in sliced sausage.
Grease a 9-inch round baking pan and pour in batter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix together potatoes, eggs, pickles and onion.
Add mayonnaise and mustard as you wish.
Salt to taste.
Mix all together.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and cream together, then add eggs. Combine sour milk, lemon juice and add to bananas.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add bananas and mix alternately with dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Grease 9 1/4 x 5 3/4 x 2 3/4-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: quick chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place dry ingredients in a large bowl. Melt margarine; pour into dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix again.
Stir in the chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart. Bake in oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Centers will be soft because of cake mix.
Cool on baking rack.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine flour, margarine and pecans well (will be stiff) and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Bake at 325°.
Let cool.

title: seven up pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Grease and lightly flour a Bundt or tube pan. Combine butter, oil, and sugar in mixer bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour, 7-Up, and lemon extract.
Mix well.
Spoon into pan and bake for 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean when inserted into center of cake.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes. Invert onto cake plate.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: cocktail punch
directions: Add water to frozen juice as directed.
Combine other juices. Chill.
Serve in punch bowl.
Float in block of ice.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: cucumber mousse
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients and let chill for 45 minutes.
Add cucumber and blend with ingredients with mixer.
Add mayonnaise and sour cream.
Place in mold sprayed with Pam cooking spray and chill until ready to serve.

title: tunamato dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package. Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Add to dinner with tuna, tomatoes, parsley and salt.
Heat for 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: tuna fish
directions: Get the eggs, mayonnaise, the tuna fish and dill pickle.
You cut the pickles and crack the eggs.
Open the tuna fish and put it in a bowl.
Put the eggs in a bowl and put in the microwave; get it out.
Put the mayonnaise in the eggs and then put the pickles in the tuna fish in a bowl.
Then you hafta mix it up.

title: ten bean soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix and soak overnight.
Drain beans and add 2 quarts water and next 4 ingredients.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender. Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 8 cups.

title: chess squares
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl, including melted margarine.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan the margarine was melted in.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cake falls.
Cake must fall to be done.

title: honey-milk fried chicken
directions: Put cut up parts of chicken in large round bowl.
Mix milk, water, salt, pepper, molasses or honey (honey preferred) together; pour over chicken.
Put in fridge; let set for 1 hour.
Have flour in flat container.
Take chicken out of milk; roll in flour, then put in medium-high oil pan and cook on medium heat until brown on both sides.
Turn heat to medium; cook for 10 or 15 minutes, until done.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet n tangy freezer pickles
directions: In a large container, combine cucumbers, onions, green pepper and 2 tablespoons salt. Cover with crushed ice; mix well. Refrigerate for 8 hours. Drain; rinse and drain again. In a saucepan, combine the sugar, vinegar, celery seed and remaining salt. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute. Spoon over cucumber mixture. Pour into jars or freezer containers. Cool. Top with lids. Cover and freeze for up to 6 weeks. Thaw at room temperature for 4 hours before serving. Makes 4 pints.

title: chili
directions: Crumble and brown ground meat.
Put meat and all other ingredients in crock-pot and stir together.
Allow to simmer for at least 2 hours.
(Can also be prepared on the stove.
Simmer for one hour.)

title: chilies rellenos with picadillo
directions: To prepare Picadillo:
In a large skillet, saute the onion, garlic and bay leaves in oil over moderate heat, stirring, until the onion is softened.
Add the beef, and continue to cook until beef is no longer pink; break up any lumps with a wooden spoon. Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in oregano, cloves, and cinnamon.
Pour out any excess fat and stir into the tomato paste until thoroughly incorporated.
Add chipotles, raisins, almonds, and olives; salt to taste.
Remove from heat.
When mixture is cooked, add cheese and mix well.
Char the flesh of the peppers over a gas flame, under a broiler or on a grill.
Alternatively, set a rack over an electric burner or use a very hot heavy frying pan.
Cook, turning frequently, until the skins are blistered all over.
Take care not to overcook and burn right through the pepper. Put peppers in a bowl, cover with plastic wrap and let sweat for about 10 minutes to loosen the skins.
Rub off as much skin as possible and cut a slit along the side of each pepper, keeping the stems and tip intact.
Carefully remove the seeds and inner membranes, but do not rinse with water.

title: swiss chicken and stuffing
directions: Cook stuffing according to instructions on the box. Meanwhile, layer the other ingredients in a 9 x 13 pan in the order listed. Drop teaspoonfuls of prepared stuffing evenly over all. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Wash and dry tomatoes; slice or chunk and remove seeds (if desired).
Put tomatoes and sugar in layers in kettle; let stand until sugar is dissolved.
Cook a few minutes.
Add thinly sliced lemon (remove seeds) and salt; cook until thick.
Cook slow and stir often.
Cinnamon may be added.
Put in clear, hot cans and seal.
If desired, can use red or yellow tomatoes or mix for a pretty color.

title: caramel apples
directions: Pare but do not peel crisp red apples; cut in eighths.
Melt Kraft caramels with a little water in pan (this sticks and burns easily, be careful).
Use own fork to skewer apple and dip in caramel.
Skewer apple (stem end first) on green stick.
Hold over hot coals until skin is puffed up and loose.
Remove peeling and roll in brown sugar.
Hold over fire until sugar bubbles.
Wrap an apple and 4 or 5 caramels in foil and put on embers.

title: my mom's bread pudding
directions: Butter slices of bread.
Cut up an place in a large mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Beat the bread and custard mixture until crumbly; pour into greased casserole. sprinkle with cinnamon and bake at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Pour in pie crust. Bake until firm (about 1 hour) at 300°. Beat egg whites. Put on top.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, margarine, milk and salt in saucepan. Heat to boiling. Boil 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add all other ingredients. Mix well and drop by heaping teaspoonful onto waxed paper.

title: double fudge chip cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and then flour 2 large or 4 to 5 small loaf pans.
Combine flour, sugar, cocoa and baking soda in large bowl and stir well.
Add buttermilk, mayonnaise and vanilla and beat until smooth.
Stir in chips; pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes for small pans or 50 to 55 minutes for large loaves.

title: leche flan
directions: Combine brown sugar and water in saucepan; stir until caramelized.
Pour half into mold.
Beat eggs slightly and add to mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat. Strain through a cloth into mold.
Place mold in a pan of water and continue heating for about 1 1/2 hours.
Allow to cool thoroughly before unmolding.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Put into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: schnitzel beans
directions: Fry bacon until brown.
Crumble.
Add sugar and vinegar to crumbled bacon and fat.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Add greens beans and onion.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: sassy meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray a loaf pan with cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine beef, salsa, oatmeal, carrots, tomatoes and mushrooms. Shape mixture into loaf. Place in loaf pan. Bake until browned and a knife inserted in the center comes out clean and hot, about 1 hour and 5 minutes. Let stand about 10 minutes before slicing.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to package directions.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350° on greased baking sheet.
Cool.

title: deer hunter's cookies
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Place ingredients, layer by layer, in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done.

title: appetizer dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in 350° oven until bubbly.
Broil to brown, if desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable marinated salad(no cooking involved)
directions: Mix
together
sugar, Sunlite oil, apple cider vinegar, salt and
poppy seed.
Mix all these and pour over the chopped vegetables.
Refrigerate
at least 3 hours before serving, but preferably	overnight.
Keep refrigerated.	Stir every now and then.

title: no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together for one minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and enjoy.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Combine water, yeast, salt and sugar; let stand until dissolved.
Add shortening and flour.
Mix and turn out onto lightly floured surface.
Knead.
Shape rolls and let stand 1 hour.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Scald milk with butter.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Blend well. Pour mixture over crumbs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden.
Serve warm or cold.

title: caramel layer cocoa squares
directions: Melt caramels and milk in a saucepan.
Mix cake mix, oleo and water together until crumbly.
Press 1/2 of dough in bottom of greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Spread chocolate chips on baked crust, then spread caramel mixture on. Sprinkle remaining dough on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool and serve.

title: roasted peppers(peperoni arrostiti)
directions: Roast peppers under broiler
or on outside grill, until skin blisters and chars.
Place
peppers
in paper bag and let sit for 5 minutes.
Peel peppers and remove seeds.
Peel under running water, if necessary.
Cut peppers in long thin strips. Arrange in platter,
overlapping peppers.
Sprinkle with olive oil, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
Serve at room temperature with fresh Italian
bread,
if
desired.
These
are also great over grilled Italian
sausage
(see recipe).
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together the margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to margarine mixture and mix in well.
Stir in oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop big rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes for a chewy cookie.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; remove to wire rack.

title: oatmeal drop biscuits
directions: Stir thoroughly the flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in oats.
Combine egg, milk and honey.
Add all at once to dry mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: Stew chicken in salted water for 1 hour.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Save 1/2 cup of liquid from broccoli.
Toss bread crumbs in 1 stick melted margarine. Combine mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and broccoli juice.
Arrange in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer 1/2 of chicken on bottom of casserole.
Top with broccoli and layer with rest of chicken on top.
Pour mayonnaise mixture over top and bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes with crumbs on top.

title: pineapple upside cake
directions: Melt butter and sugar in skillet.
Arrange pineapple, nuts and cherries as needed to cover bottom of skillet.

title: italian fish stew
directions: Heat oil in 2-quart pot.
Add onion, pepper, celery, garlic, herbs, clove and pepper.
Stir-fry on medium heat 3 minutes until onion softens.
Add tomato juice and tomatoes and bring to simmer. Put fish chunks in layer on top.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in fish chunks in layer on top.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in fish chunks, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 cups; serves 4 to 6. Serve with Italian bread and a salad.
Fish should be haddock, cod or whitefish.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: meringue mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In small bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add salt, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Beat until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating at high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fill pastry bag fitted with large writing tip with meringue.
Pipe 15 mounds resembling "caps" of mushrooms (1 to 1 1/2 inches) on a foil-lined sheet.
Pipe 15 "stems" (1 to 1 1/2 inches long).
Sift cocoa mix over caps and stems.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix lemon juice with apples.
Put 1/3 of bread in greased 8 x 8-inch dish.
Cover with 1 cup apples, 1/4 cup cottage cheese, 1/2 raisins plus some cinnamon.
Mix milk powder, egg and sugar.
Pour 1 cup over dish.
Repeat bread, apples and liquid; end with bread.
Pour last of milk mixture over top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot margarine on top.
Let sit 20 minutes or longer.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Let sit 10 to 20 minutes at room temperature.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate pecan wafers
directions: Mix shortening, salt and vanilla.
Add sugar and cream mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add melted chocolate and flour. Mix in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Let stand a few minutes.
Press with a fork dipped in cold water. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a light boil.
Cool.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Cover with meringue and brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, blend sugar and oil.
Beat in the eggs, one at a time.
Add zucchini and set aside.
Combine the dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased 3 1/2 x 6 x 2 loaf pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into cakes.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dressing for slaw served by altrusa
directions: Tartness will vary with type of vinegar used.
We used distilled white vinegar.
We have used apple cider vinegar. Flavored vinegars are good (tarragon, wine, etc.).

title: date nut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Add cinnamon to flour; sift into wet.
Add dates and walnuts.
Drop by tablespoons on sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or less.

title: apple butter
directions: Wash, remove stems and quarter apples.
Add cider.
Cook slowly until apples are soft.
Put apples through a sieve.
Measure 1/2 to 2/3 cup of sugar for each cup of pulp to taste.
Add spices.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar dissolves.
Continue to cook, stirring often, until mixture sheets from spoon.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar and mix.
Add 6 cups milk and salt.
Cook until well blended and hot to touch, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add condensed milk, half and half and vanilla.
Mix well, then add bananas and cherries.
Pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: butter bean creole
directions: Mix butter beans with tomato soup, onions and green peppers. Place in greased casserole pan and arrange sausage links on top. Bake in oven at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: creamy cucumber slices
directions: Mix salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Add sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Fold in onions, parsley and cucumber slices. Arrange on a flat dish.
Chill for an hour or longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: slow cooker chicken
directions: Prepare dressing as directed.
Set aside to cool.
Stir in wine.
Blanch carrots 5 minutes in boiling water.
Drain and put in crock-pot.
Stuff chicken with dressing and place in pot over carrots.
Cover pot and set on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shortcakes
directions: Combine ingredients to soft dough.
Place by large tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Served with fruit, mainly strawberries over.
Makes 6 nice shortcakes.

title: green chili
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces.
Brown pork with garlic and onions.
Stir in flour.
Add beans, juice and chilies; cook (the longer it cooks, the hotter and better it gets).

title: orange and onion salad
directions: Soak onions in salted ice water while you peel and slice oranges and avocado.
Drain onion slices and arrange alternately with orange and avocado slices on top of lettuce.
Pour French dressing over all.
Serve with chili con carne or any rich meat dish.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and slice in a pan. Slice onions to taste. Salt and pepper to taste. Put oleo in slices on top. Cover with plastic wrap and microwave until done. Heat oven to 425°.
Bake potatoes uncovered until crispy. Put chopped chives and cheese on top. Melt cheese. Top with sour cream.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook until hard ball forms when dropped into a cup of cool water.
Remove from heat and add cornflakes.
Butter a long pan and press cookie mixture in it. Let cool. Eat and enjoy.

title: cheesy party mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine cereal, pretzels and peanuts.
Pour butter over cereal mixture, mixing well. Spread with cheese and onion powder; toss well to coat.
Spread into an ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: mountain mamma
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Be sure it browns, then cool.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter and the chocolate in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook over low heat until butter and chocolate are melted. Remove from heat and cool to room temperature. Sift together 1 cup flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and salt. Stir dry ingredients into cooled chocolate mixture. Add 2 eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla, blending well. Stir in 1 cup walnuts. Spread batter in a well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Combine cream cheese and 1/4 cup butter in a bowl. Beat until smooth and creamy, using electric mixer. Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.

Add to cream cheese mixture, beating well. Beat in 1 egg and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spread over batter. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup walnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Cool in pan. Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars. Makes 24 brownies.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute onion in melted butter in large skillet until tender (do not brown).
Add tomatoes, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Combine with macaroni and mix well.
Turn mixture into greased 3-quart casserole, alternating layers of macaroni mixture and cheese, ending with cheese layer. Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: garlic croutons
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam.
Spread cubes on cookie sheet.
Spray cubes with Pam.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Stir a little to coat.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes until dry, crisp and golden brown.
Stir occasionally.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Top with bacon. Bake 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: slaw
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Let cool and pour over vegetables.

title: frosty fruit smoothie
directions: In a blender container, combine the banana chunks, chilled fruit juice, milk, vanilla and ice cubes.
Cover and blend until frothy.
Pour mixture into glasses.
Serve immediately.

title: spiced pot roast
directions: Place meat in a large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix cider, brown sugar, cloves, ginger and cinnamon; pour over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Remove meat from marinade and pat dry with paper towel.

title: queen mary's apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples in pie shell.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together and sprinkle over apples.
Combine flour and 1/2 cup sugar and cut butter in until consistency of crumbs.
Bake at 400° approximately 45 minutes.
(Pack flour and sugar mixture over sliced apples.)

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix together flour and salt.
Add drops of food coloring to water and add water slowly; mix well.
Add oil and knead mixture together.
You might need to add more flour or water to get proper consistency.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Keeps for many weeks!
Great for that rainy Saturday.

title: texas barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine tomato juice, vinegar, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, brown sugar, paprika, onion salt, mustard, pepper and hot sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Brush on chicken. Makes about 2 cups sauce.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco together. Add eggs and flour alternating, ending with an egg. Add vanilla and beat good. Bake in tube pan at 250° for 2 hours.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and butter.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Stir in egg yolks and milk and mix.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole or individual baking cups. Bake in pan with 1-inch of hot water surrounding it.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hamburger-potato scallop
directions: In medium skillet, brown meat with salt over medium heat; drain.
Stir in potatoes; sprinkle with packet of seasoned sauce mix.
Add amounts of water and milk called for on package.
Stir in pimiento and green pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring frequently. Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: In small saucepan, heat first three ingredients until warm (120° to 130°).
In large bowl combine warm liquid, 2 cups plain flour, 1 cup wheat flour and remaining ingredients, beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
By hand stir in remaining wheat flour and enough plain flour to make a stiff dough.

title: cheese-garlic biscuits
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large bowl with electric mixer.
Stir well.
Heat milk and margarine until very warm, 120° to 130°.
Gradually add to dry ingredients and beat at low speed, scraping sides of bowl, 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat at moderate speed, scraping sides of bowl, 2 minutes.
With spoon, stir in remaining flour to make soft dough. Batter will be thick, but not stiff.
Cover and let rise 1 hour or until doubled.
Stir down and spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes or until doubled. Bake at 350° to 400° for about 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: celery loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a greased pan 40 minutes at 400°.
Serve with mushroom, cream or onion gravy.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix together and let set for a while before serving.
Keep refrigerated.
Serve with Town House crackers.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar together until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread on pretzel layer.
Chill.
Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Stir in strawberries.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes.
When partially set, pour on top of Cool Whip in pan.
Cover and chill.

title: chicken picata
directions: Chop and saute the first 4 ingredients. Remove from pan.
Make thin chicken cutlets. Dredge in mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Fry cutlets in mixture of 1/2 olive oil and 1/2 butter on medium-high heat. Remove from pan.
Pour the wine in hot pan to glaze. Add the chicken broth, lemon juice and capers.
Stir while heating.
Replace cutlets and onion mixture. This should thicken gravy.
If too thick, add chicken broth to thin it.

title: linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine, rinse with cold water; drain.
Mix linguine with one bottle of Salad Supreme (you'll find this with the spices in the supermarket).

title: fruit tea
directions: Mix all ingredients in a gallon pitcher and fill with water. Serve over ice.

title: one egg cake(depression era - 1930's)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream the shortening with sugar until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: nutritional oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Form dough into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These cookies are so nutritional they can be eaten for breakfast and are a real good snack for after school.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour four 1-pound coffee cans.
Sift dry ingredients together; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients. Slowly add dry ingredients to batter while mixing.
Pour into coffee cans (1/2 full).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: hash 'n cheese grill
directions: Mix hash, catsup, onion, parsley flakes and oregano; spread on muffin halves.
Top with cheese strips.
Set oven control at broil and/or 550°.
Broil 8 to 10 inches from heat until cheese is melted and hash mixture is bubbly and hot.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: calamondin orange pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in heavy saucepan.
Stir in milk and cook over medium heat (stirring constantly) until thick.
Add small amount (approximately 1/2 cup) of this mixture to egg yolks.
Pour this back into saucepan, stirring thoroughly.
Cook over medium heat to boiling point.
Remove from heat and stir in orange puree and butter.
Bring back to boiling point.
Remove and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with meringue and brown top at 350°.

title: world's most delicious cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream together butter, sugars and egg. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients in order given, except pecans.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans.
You may form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten with fork.
Bake at 325° to 350° according to your oven for 15 minutes, until just lightly browned.
Do not overcook.
Let cool a few minutes before removing from pans. Makes approximately 6 dozen cookies.

title: hearty casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ground beef, onion and celery in skillet.
Cook until browned.
Add rice, soups, water and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir together and put in greased two quart casserole.
Top with chow mein noodles and bake 40 to 45 minutes. Use small can of noodles.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add along with milk and flavorings.
Mix well and pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Sprinkle coconut over top of each pie.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Combine soups, broth and chiles.
Add chicken and mix well.
Fry tortillas lightly on each side. Remove.
Place a layer of tortillas (in 9 x 13-inch pan), layer of chicken sauce and a layer of cheese.
Repeat layering until pan is filled, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil.
Cook to 236°.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Stir until blended.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: coconut squares(a moroccan taste treat.)
directions: Combine the coconut, half and half and the sugar in a heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil, then heat to low. Simmer until a soft ball is formed when a spoon full is dropped into cold water. Add the butter and lemon rind and mix. Let cool to room temperature. Transfer to a bowl and with an electric mixer, mix the batter until thick
and glossy. Pour into a small buttered pan and chill. Cut into squares and serve.

title: cooked okra
directions: Wash okra and cut off stems.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices and place in saucepan.
Add salt, cover with water and cook, uncovered, 15 to 25 minutes.
Drain.
To serve, season with pepper, butter and vinegar.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add bananas and nuts.
Add flour sifted with soda.
Blend well.
Bake in loaf pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: easy berry smoothie
directions: Combine pineapple, banana, milk and strawberries in blender or food processor container. Cover and blend until smooth. Garnish with banana slice and strawberry, if desired. Makes 3 servings.

title: dip for fresh fruit
directions: In small bowl, stir together the first 5 ingredients.
Makes 6 (3 tablespoon) servings.

title: butterscotch chip cake
directions: Mix together first three items and pour into a greased and floured cake pan.
Then sprinkle over the top the last three items and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crunchy broccoli-cauliflower toss
directions: Combine, cauliflower, broccoli, bacon and cheese in bowl. Set aside.
In a small bowl, combine Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar mix until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mix.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill about an hour before serving.

title: heath's hot fudge cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into an ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Next, mix the brown sugar with the cocoa.
Sprinkle over cake.
Pour 2 cups of water over the cake. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken cordon blue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lay out chicken breast on a flat surface and pound chicken until slightly flat.
In each flattened breast add 1/2 piece of ham and 1/2 piece of cheese.
Roll up carefully and place a toothpick in each roll to hold them in place.
Place seam side down in pan.
Add 1/2 cup milk to both cans of soup and mix well; pour over chicken and cook uncovered for 1 hour.
Great for entertaining.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken with salt and pepper in approximately 2 quarts water until tender.
Skin, debone and cut into large bite-size pieces.
Cook the bell pepper, celery and onions in the broth until celery starts to tenderize; add the spaghetti and cook until tender.
Add the chicken chunks, pimentos and cream of mushroom soup.
Stir and mix well.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Add Cheez Whiz for garnish (drop by spoonfuls across the top).
Heat in warm oven 20 to 30 minutes or until cheese melts or lightly browns before serving.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef in mixing bowl.
Add bread, water, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Fry in frying pan until golden brown.
Mix in a saucepan the tomato soup and sugar and boil.
Then add meatballs.
Serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine together and refrigerate overnight in long, flat baking dish.
Take out of refrigerator one hour before baking. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add carrots and egg.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add to wet mixture.
Add vanilla and almond extract.

title: stuffed peppers with spanish rice
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise and core.
Parboil 7 to 8 minutes until just beginning to get tender.
Drain and place in a baking dish.
Set aside.
Brown meat, onion and garlic together in a frying pan.
Drain off any fat.
Add tomato paste and simmer about 10 minutes.
Stuff the peppers with about 2/3 of the meat mixture. To the remaining meat, add rice, chilies and tomatoes.
Simmer until rice is tender, about 6 to 7 minutes.
Spoon the rice around the peppers; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake 30 minutes until peppers are fully cooked.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pesto pita pizzas
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Place 2 oven racks in bottom half of oven.
Remove fajitas from packaging and place in a microwave safe dish.
Heat on HIGH power until pieces begin to thaw; stir and rearrange fajitas in dish as necessary.
Pull apart to separate; tear or cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Meanwhile, line 2 large baking sheets with foil.
Lay 3 pita shells on each baking sheet.
Combine mayonnaise with pesto; spread evenly over tops of pita bread, about 2 tablespoons on each.
Place chicken, artichoke hearts, and mushrooms over pesto layer.
Cut pepper into thin strips; lay strips over tops of pizzas and sprinkle evenly with cheese, 1/3 cup over each pizza.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, or until cheese melts and begins to brown.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes, cut into slices and serve.

title: deep dish beans
directions: Brown sausage, cut into pieces and drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Put bacon on top.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 325°. Makes quite a lot but freezes well.
Also good to cook in crock-pot.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix together flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Pat into pizza pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: savory corncakes
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Beat together creamed corn, egg, milk and oil and stir into the dry mixture.
Do not overmix. Let batter rest, refrigerated, for an hour or more before proceeding.

title: best banana bread
directions: Blend sugar, butter (margarine) and egg. Add bananas.
Mix flour and baking soda; add.
Add nuts (if desired).
Pour into greased bread pan and bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: golden sherbet punch
directions: Combine sugar, mint and boiling water; stir to dissolve sugar. Chill.
Strain into chilled punch bowl.
Add lemon juice, apricot nectar and concentrates.
Pour ginger ale down sides of punch bowl.
Top with scoops of sherbet.
Garnish with fresh mint. Serves 20 to 25.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Blend well; put cheese mixture in 1 unbaked 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Spread 1 cup chopped pecans, then pour mixture over nuts.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until center is firm.

title: german pancake
directions: Work butter and flour on a board until consistency of cornmeal.
Add all other ingredients and carefully work into a dough, mixing everything well.
It helps to add a little at a time and work in well.
Let rest in fridge several hours, or overnight.

title: party punch
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.

title: easy chicken and pasta
directions: In skillet, heat 1 Tbsp. oil.
Add chicken and cook until browned.
Add soup, 1/2 c. water and vegetable combination.
Cover and cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Serves 4

title: low-fat beef stroganoff
directions: Slice beef in thin diagonal strips (may be easier to do if partially frozen).
Mix flour and paprika, shake beef strips in it to coat.
Brown beef, onion and garlic in oil over high heat until brown.
Stir in mushrooms, yogurt and bouillon cube.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve over macaroni ribbons.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mustard sauce(sennepsaus)
directions: Use dill weed if fresh dill is not in season.

title: party pat
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until smooth. Spread on party rye bread or snack crackers.

title: sausage supper
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan, drain and crumble.
Add vegetables and seasonings to pan drippings.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes, tossing frequently. Add kielbasa slices and water.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender, tossing occasionally.
Sprinkle bacon on top.
Serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together, then pour it into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until brown on top.

title: "cheating" marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and milk; mix well until blended.
Gradually add sugar.
Stir in chocolate, vanilla and salt.
Fold in marshmallows.
Drop rounded teaspoonful of mixture on baking sheet.
Chill until firm.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and honey.
Sift dry ingredients and spices together.
Add to mixture alternating with 1/2 cup milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites, then add almonds, figs and raisins.
Pour into well-greased lightly floured bread loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes until test straw comes out clean.

title: half-moon cookies
directions: Mix with a beater and drop by heaping spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Turn upside down to cool.
Frost 1/2 of flat side with chocolate frosting and 1/2 with vanilla frosting.
These freeze well.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Let berries and sugar come to boil or simmer a few minutes, about 10.
Then add 1 large package wildberry strawberry jello; stir well.
Then put into jars.

title: easy broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in
casserole in order listed.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: india chicken and rice
directions: Pick the meat
off the bones of a larger fryer or young hen. Cut the
meat
into
small cubes, put it into heavy iron pot.
Add 1
teaspoon
salt, 1/2 teaspoon black pepper, onion (chopped) and no
water.
Mix
well
together and simmer on a very slow heat until the meat is tender.
Mix often but do not brown it.
Cook the
bones in another pot in about 1 quart of water, 1 teaspoon salt and garlic.
When the meat on the bone is cooked, strain
the broth into the meat you had cooked; if more water
is
needed, add
some.
Add
coconut.
In a small bowl, mix
flour,
curry powder, cumin powder, ground ginger, cayenne pepper and nutmeg; mix well.
Add cold water to make a thin paste, put
in the stew and cook about 10 minutes more on a very slow
fire.
If
too thick,
add more water.
Serve on steamed rice.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: In a large bowl, mix drained canned vegetables. Add onions, peppers, celery, and cucumber. Then cover with dressing. Cover bowl and chill overnight. Drain before serving.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat room temperature cream cheese until smooth.
Add eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 357° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: bunk house chili
directions: Brown beef in oil and drain. Add remaining ingredients, except for beans, and simmer 1 hour. Add beans and continue to simmer 45 additional minutes. If liquid is too thin, 1 can of tomato paste can be added to thicken.

title: batter for fried shrimp
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add water and oil.
Beat until smooth. Fold in egg white just before frying.
Coat fan-tail shrimp and fry in deep fat until brown.

title: sloppy joes(kids dishes)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Butter lightly the hamburger buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil and heat in oven for 15 minutes.
Brown in skillet the ground beef; stir in tomato soup, mustard and salt. Simmer over heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into warm buns.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: p'nut butter balls
directions: Cream oleo and peanut butter.
Stir in sugar.
Cool and shape into balls and dip in chocolate.

title: pumpkin custard cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Grease bottom only of 13 x 9-inch pan.
In larger mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, water and 3 eggs.
Blend and beat as directed on package.
Pour into prepared pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat pumpkin and 2 eggs.
Pour evenly over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill.
Serve on fish, French fries or as a dip.

title: diet delight
directions: Mix dry jello and cottage cheese.
Stir in pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: taco soup
directions: Using a 4 to 5 qt. soup pan, brown meat and drain.
May want to microwave meat first to extract fat and then brown along with onions.
Stir the 2 dry mixes into meat mixture.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Heat to serving temperature.
Feel free to add more beans and corn.
Freezes well. (Approximately 14 servings.)

title: taco dip(great!)
directions: Make bed of lettuce; then layer as follows:
Combine sour cream and taco mix.
Pile on lettuce.
