Mix bean dip, 2 tablespoons of reserved sour cream and jalapeno pepper (chopped fine), if desired. Mix avocado, garlic powder, lemon juice and last 2 tablespoons of sour cream.
Put on top of bean dip mix.
Last layer is combination of tomato, cheese, onions and olives.
Sprinkle lots of taco sauce on top.
Enjoy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt and baking powder together; stir in nuts and wheat bran.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Combine mashed bananas and sour cream; add alternatively with flour to first mixture.
Bake in a greased loaf pan lined with waxed paper in a moderate oven on 350° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix fruit and stir in honey.
Let it stand in a cool place for 2 or 3 hours.

title: charlie's secret soup
directions: In a saucepan, heat peanut butter and butter on low heat. When melted, stir in flour and wheat germ.
Remove from heat and blend in milk.
Add mashed banana and salt.
Return to heat and cook over low heat for 7 minutes to blend flavors.
Add sliced banana and cook 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Serve hot.
Makes 2 servings.

title: double apple muffins
directions: Stir together flour, cereal, sugar substitute, baking powder, soda and spice; set aside.

title: ginger bake
directions: Mix molasses, sugar,
lard,
eggs and flour and ginger. Add soda.
Mix well.
On this pour boiling water and mix well. Bake at 350° until done.

title: english muffin pizzas
directions: Split muffins in half.
Spread sauce on each muffin; add pepperoni and top with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Put under broiler for 1 to 2 minutes until cheese is hot and bubbly.
Yields 8 servings.

title: low-carb stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Clean the mushrooms. Remove their stems and use a paring knife to make the hole for stuffing larger. Brown and drain the sausage and stir in the cream cheese. Spoon the mixture into the mushroom caps. Bake for 20 minutes. Yield: About 30 mushrooms.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Early in day, cook carrots until barely tender; drain.
Melt butter in saucepan and cook onion in butter 20 or 30 minutes. Stir in flour, salt and mustard.
Add milk and cook, stirring until smooth.
Add pepper and celery salt.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange layers of carrots and cheese alternately. Repeat until all are used, ending with carrots.
Pour on sauce. Top with crumbs.
Refrigerate about 3/4 hour.
Before serving, bake in 350° oven for about 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Sift half of dry ingredients into sugar mixture; blend.
Sift in remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add carrots and mix well, then mix in pecans.
Pour in three 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Frost with Coconut Pecan Frosting.

title: low-fat peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Using a mixer, mix all wet ingredients.
Add dry to wet ingredients.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes. Makes 2 dozen.

title: faith's ham strata
directions: Defrost and drain broccoli.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Cut crusts from bread and layer 6 slices from bread and layer 6 slices in bottom of dish.
Next, put a layer of cheese, broccoli and then ham.
Top with remaining bread.
Mix milk, eggs and salt. Pour over bread and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
The next morning bake at 325° for 50 minutes uncovered.
Take out and put extra cheese on top.
Put back in oven for 10 more minutes.
Cover with foil and let stand for 10 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Make a space in the center of the bowl, pushing the dry ingredients to the sides of the bowl and add the eggs, vanilla and strawberries.
Mix everything together well. Pour batter into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for approximately 60 minutes or until center is baked.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut cabbage leaves from stalk.
Place in large pan of boiling water for several minutes to soften; drain.
Combine meat, rice, onion, egg, salt and pepper; mix well.
Spoon mixture onto cabbage leaves; roll to enclose filling and fasten with wooden pick. Combine water and tomato juice in large pot.
Lay rolls in pot; cook for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours on medium heat.
The last 20 minutes of cooking time, add the sauerkraut.

title: potluck potato salad
directions: Pour French dressing over warm potatoes.
Chill 2 hours.
Add celery, onion, egg and salt.
Add salad dressing and mix carefully.
Add 1 teaspoon celery seed if desired.
Chill 4 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients (except cheese and cornbread batter). Simmer 15 minutes.
Spread cheese on top of hamburger mixture. Stir up cornbread batter and pour on top of mixture with cheese. Bake in 375° oven until cornbread is done.
Serve with lettuce and sour cream.

title: curried rice with beef
directions: Cooking Time: 1 hour.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and cheese well.
Add sugar gradually and continue creaming.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and orange peel. Sift flour with salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture.
Fill cookie press; form fancy cookies on ungreased cookie sheet. Decorate with colored sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: cap'n crunch treats
directions: Melt white almond bark in microwave.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Spoon out onto wax paper. Cool, then break apart.

title: peanut butter, chocolate chip, rice krispies treats
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Stir flour, cocoa and baking powder into egg mixture.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top and bake 3 minutes; cool.

title: cheese dip
directions: Saute onion in margarine; reduce heat to low.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until process cheese spread is melted.
Serve hot with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: raspberry applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce.
Remove from heat.
Stir in gelatin until dissolved.
Add orange juice and pineapple.
Add celery and nuts. Chill until ready to serve.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash up avocado with potato masher.
Add other stuff and mix well.

title: rolls
directions: Mix until set. Let rise about 45 minutes. Roll out.
Put in buttered pan. Butter the tops.
Let rise about 30 minutes. Bake slowly until brown.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift the flour and baking powder together, then add alternately with the buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: crunchy stuffed eggs
directions: Peel eggs; slice in half lengthwise and carefully remove yolks.
Mash yolks and stir in sour cream, salt, pepper and parsley.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in bacon.
Stuff eggs with yolk mixture and sprinkle with paprika and top with olive.

title: festive sweet potatoes
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Remove from heat, stir in strawberries and pour into crust.
Refrigerate until firm, then top with Cool Whip.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with sides (or jelly roll pan or broiler pan bottom) with aluminum foil. Spray foil with cooking spray. Cover bottom of pan with single layer of crackers. Set aside.

title: minute steak stew
directions: Cut steaks into 1-inch strips.
Season flour with salt and pepper.
Roll steak in flour mixture.
Heat butter in skillet until bubbling.
Add meat; brown well on all sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cut whole potatoes into cubes.
Cover skillet; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: violet's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Mix egg, sugar, salt and flour.
Work in melted Crisco.
Place in large mixing bowl and let rise double.
Refrigerate and bake as needed.

title: smiling sugar cookies
directions: Roll dough into 1 1/2 inch balls, insert a wooden stick in center of each.
Place 2 inches apart on slightly greased cookie sheet, flatten slightly.
Bake according to dough directions, until lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire racks and cool.
Divide frosting into 3 bowls.
Tint with color.
Place each color frosting in separate and resealable bags.
Cut small hole in corner of bag.
Pipe in hair and a smile, use a dab of frosting to attach small candies for nose and eyes.
Let dry for at least 30 minutes.

title: jai's disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Grease 8 or 9-inch baking pan with shortening.
Melt butter over low heat.
In mixing bowl, combine sugar and cocoa.
Stir in melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Add flour and salt and mix just until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Scrape the mixture into the greased pan and spread out.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes, just until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool in pan before cutting.

title: vegetable and chip dip
directions: Combine all and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: southwestern chicken skillet
directions: Cook chicken in large nonstick skillet on medium heat until cooked through, stirring occasionally. Stir in macaroni and 2 cups of water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer until
water is almost gone. Add Velveeta and tomatoes. Cook until cheese is melted, stirring frequently. Remove from heat; stir in sour cream. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook and drain well the spinach per package directions; set aside.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add Accent and milk; blend.
Add other ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden and firm.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat to a boil.
Mixture will be bubbling all over.
Boil and stir for 5 minutes more.
Take off heat.
Stir in 6 ounce package semi-sweet chocolate bits until completely melted.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup chopped nuts. Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: swiss steak quickie
directions: *May use 1 can mushroom soup, undiluted.

title: dump cake
directions: Use a 9 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish. Dump pineapple in dish and spread over bottom of dish. Dump cherry pie filling over pineapple and spread evenly. Dump 1 box of yellow cake mix (dry) over pie filling; spread evenly. Sprinkle 1 cup chopped nuts over mixture. Slice 2 sticks of margarine over mixture, placing evenly on top of cake. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and put bacon on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over margarine.
Mix together and press into pan.
Pour condensed milk in.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash squash and add other ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt butter and mix all ingredients together, except chocolate bar.
Spread into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Melt chocolate; spread over top.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: baked pecans
directions: Beat egg white until stiff. Add sugar and vanilla to egg white. Mix well and coat pecans. Melt butter on cookie sheet. Pour pecans onto pan, single layer. Bake 10 minutes.
Salt lightly and turn over.
Bake 10 minutes.
Salt lightly. Turn over and bake 10 minutes.
Total baking time:
30 minutes.

title: not your ordinary meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, pepper, ketchup and eggs.
Add enough crackers to make mixture dry, yet moist enough to hold together.
Form into a loaf; place into a baking dish.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of water around base.
Mix ketchup and brown sugar together to form a paste; spread over top of meat loaf.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove foil; bake 30 minutes more. Drain off excess water.
Slice and serve.

title: georgia chewy pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Baking time is 15 minutes.

title: make in the blender wild rice pancakes
directions: Into blender container, put 1/4 cup wild rice.
Cover and blend 60 seconds on high.
Add eggs, milk, flour and salt.
Blend on high for 30 seconds.
Fry on hot griddle with plenty of butter.
(Make small pancakes, about 3 inches in diameter.)
Drain on absorbent paper, fold in quarters.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, or serve with favorite jam.
May be served cold as an hors d'oeuvre.
Great for an afternoon tea.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil for about 4 minutes. Remove from burner and add oats.
Stir well and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: cocktail franks(makes 72 franks)
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat 1 cup flour into cooled milk until smooth.
Add yeast.
Let stand until light and bubbly.

title: coconut macaroons cake
directions: Put egg whites in large bowl and beat at high speed until soft peaks.
Set aside.
Combine egg yolks, shortening and margarine until well blended.
Gradually beat in sugar and salt.
Add flavoring and beat in flour and milk.
Add coconut and fold in egg whites.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.

title: no lump gravy(thanksgiving)
directions: Melt butter with flour in a saucepan. Whisk in hot liquid from turkey drippings (degrease it first; supplement with chicken broth if necessary) and allow to simmer for 20 minutes.

title: mama's boiled frosting
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients over low heat; stirring until sugar dissolves.
Cover pan 2 to 3 minutes to dissolve sugar crystals on sides of pan.
Uncover.
Cook to hard ball stage (236°) or until when you drop off of spoon you see tiny threads.
Gradually add hot syrup to egg whites, beating constantly; add vanilla; beat until frosting is of spreading consistency; frost tops and sides of two (8 or 9-inch) layers.
Add coconut on top of cake.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Fry bacon until done.
Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: art's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 1 or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: irish stew
directions: Wipe meat with damp cloth; dredge in flour and brown slowly in oil on all sides.
Add 1 cup water. Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Add salt, pepper, diced potatoes, carrots and onion with 1 1/2 cups water.
Continue simmering until tender. Add parsley before serving.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Crumble cornbread in medium bowl.
Melt margarine in large skillet over medium heat. Add onion, celery and water.
Cover, reduce heat and cook 15 minutes until tender. Remove from heat. Stir in poultry seasoning, sage, salt and pepper.
Mix bread crumbs, cornbread, chicken broth, parsley and eggs. Combine mixtures.
Pour into prepared pan (2-quart casserole dish) coated with Pam and bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes until golden brown and tested with toothpick for doneness.

title: unfried french fries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Slice each potato lengthwise into 1/4-inch ovals, then slice each oval lengthwise into match sticks. Coat a baking sheet with 3 sprays of light vegetable oil cooking spray.

title: "deluxe" bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Toast bread slices lightly.
Spread with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put two toast slices together, making two sandwiches.
Remove crusts and cut each sandwich into 4 rectangles.
Arrange rectangles in single layer in casserole. Sprinkle with raisins.
Blend eggs, granulated sugar, vanilla (and salt if you use it).

title: chocolate cake
directions: Melt together the margarine and cocoa.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Heat until sugar has dissolved.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil until soft.
Add chicken broth and let it come to a boil.
Add beans and bouillon cubes.
When that comes to a boil, add the zucchini.
Let it cook slowly for 1 hour.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 4 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix apples with 2/3 cup sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, lemon peel and juice; set aside. Line 9-inch pan with 1 pastry circle. Fill with apple mixture. Dot with margarine. Cover with top crust and crimp edges. Prick top with fork. Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 50 minutes or until apples are tender. Sprinkle crust with sugar before or after baking, if desired.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Make 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm with milk!

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a medium bowl, stir together the cornmeal, oat bran, milk, egg white and oil.
Set aside for five minutes.
In a small bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir the flour mixture into the cornmeal mixture.
Divide batter evenly among 11 or 12 cups of a lightly greased or nonstick spray coated muffin tin.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until the muffins are brown.
Muffins are best served warm.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick. Add lump of butter (size of egg) and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Put in 2 cooked pie crusts.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Cut off
"boxy"
ends
of chicken and cut in half.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Place chicken in crock-pot and cook on high for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to low for an additional 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar gradually.
Then add melted oleo, pinch of salt and pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until middle is set. Do not overbake.
Pie crust; follow direction on box.

title: easy nachos
directions: To prepare cheese sauce:
Cut cheese into cubes and place in microwave-safe dish.
Melt in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add some of the milk and stir.
Repeat process until creamy.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Boil yams until tender and remove skins.
Mash and season with pinch of salt, butter and cream.
Take heaping tablespoon of potato mix; form ball, flatten and place pecan and marshmallow in center.
Mold into ball, roll in graham cracker crumbs.
Place balls on greased pan.
Just before serving, place in hot oven to brown slightly and let the marshmallows get a little soft.
Serve at once.

title: tangy fruit salad
directions: Mix tang and pudding.
Mix with fruit.
Before serving add bananas.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti almost done.
Brown hamburger.
Prepare homemade sauce or mix with jar Ragu. Combine cooked spaghetti with sauce with meat and Velveeta cheese.
Mix.
In a large casserole dish, pour mixture. Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let stand an additional 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon-lime salad
directions: Place gelatin in mixing bowl. Add boiling water, stirring to completely dissolve. Cool. When it starts to thicken add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate. Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: pepper with cream cheese filling
directions: Tip:
You can add chopped walnuts or salted peanuts to the cream mixture for another flavor.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling water until almost tender. Peel and cut in thick slices.
Place in a greased baking dish. Bring to a boil the sugar, salt, water and butter.
Pour over the sweet potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are clear and syrup is thick.
Baste occasionally to prevent top layer from drying out.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks, sugar, butter and vanilla.
Add beaten egg whites last.
Bake in oven at 375° for 45 minutes. Bake over pan with hot water.

title: nutty green salad
directions: Combine greens, zucchini, carrot and peanuts; toss.
Pour dressing over salad; toss.
Serve.

title: salmon dip
directions: Put all ingredients into blender or food processor and blend.

title: citrus punch
directions: Combine 1 cup water and sugar in a small saucepan; cook over low heat.
Cool.
Stir in pineapple juice, 3 cups water and next 2 ingredients.
Cover and chill.
Just before serving, stir in carbonated beverage.
Serve over ice cubes.
Yields 3 quarts (85 calories, 0 fat) per 6 ounce serving.

title: nutty meal starters
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Chill for 2 or 3 hours before serving. Spread thick on assorted crackers.

title: parmesan stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut off top of tomatoes.
Scoop out and put in blender until smooth.
Add all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Combine butter, Worcestershire and salts in a 3-quart casserole.
Microwave 45 seconds on High to melt butter.
Add remaining ingredients, tossing thoroughly until well coated. Microwave 3 to 4 minutes on High, tossing every 1 1/2 minutes to distribute seasoned butter. Cool and store in airtight container.

title: oven chicken dinner
directions: Brown chicken, if desired.
Add celery and chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half; remove potato filling.
Put potato filling in bowl, adding above ingredients.
Refill potato shells. Sprinkle more cheese on top of potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry delite
directions: Combine all ingredients into oblong dish.
Freeze 4 or 5 hours.
Remove 30 minutes before serving.

title: orange sauce
directions: Combine 1/4 cup of the orange juice and sugar in a pan. Bring to a boil over low heat.
Boil 1 minute and then add remaining orange juice and the margarine and orange peel.
Stir until well mixed.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Drain strawberries. Cut frozen angel food cake in half. Cut halves of cake in half again. Mix powdered sugar with enough milk to make spreading consistency. Divide powdered sugar mixture in half. Add green food coloring to 1/2 to make pale green color. Add yellow food coloring to other half to make pale yellow color. To green coloring, add mint flavoring and to yellow coloring, add lemon flavoring. Spread green mint flavored icing on top of 1 layer of cake, then stack another layer of cake on top. Mix strawberries and whipped topping together; spread some on second layer of cake. Stack another layer on top of that. Spread yellow lemon flavored icing on third layer, then top with last layer of cake. Spread remaining strawberry mixture over and around cake. Keep frozen until ready to serve.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini.
Mix lightly with remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Combine bread crumbs, ground beef, 1/2 cup onion, salt, pepper and milk.
Make into balls and place into baking dish.
Combine vinegar, sugar, ketchup, water and 1/2 cup of onion to make sauce. Set aside half of this mixture to use later.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over meatballs and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Pour other half of mixture over meatballs after taking out of oven.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil; pour jello in and let stand until dissolved and cool. Add buttermilk and Cool Whip. Mix and chill.

title: chocolate peanut balls
directions: In a bowl, stir together the brown sugar, 1/2 stick melted butter, graham cracker crumbs and peanut butter until mixture is smooth.
Chill the mixture, covered, for 1 hour or until it is firm enough to form into balls.
Form teaspoonfuls of the mixture into balls and transfer the balls as they are formed to a baking sheet lined with waxed paper.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook in large pot for 20 minutes or more the bouillon cubes, water, celery and onion.
Add the potatoes, carrots and bag of frozen vegetables (thaw and drain before adding) and cook until tender.
Add the cream of chicken soup and Velveeta cheese. Simmer slowly, stirring often, until cheese is melted.
Enjoy.

title: divinity candy
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water on high until a rolling boil; turn down.
Cook to soft ball stage, then pour hot syrup into 2 beaten egg whites.
Pour slowly.
Add vanilla.
Put chopped pecans in candy; stir until it cools and gets thick.
You have to work quickly.
It helps to have someone help dip it with teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: fluffy banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding according to instructions on box but use 1/4 cup less milk.
Add sour cream and half (8 ounces) whipped topping.
Mix well.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat until smooth.
Serve surrounded by Granny Smith apples.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Put oleo in deep cake pan and melt oleo in oven.
Stir up batter of 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour over melted oleo.
Do not stir.
Put peaches on top.
Bake about 1 hour in 350 degree oven or until golden brown.
Batter rises to top during baking.

title: sherbet punch
directions: In a punch bowl, mix Kool-Aid, ginger ale, orange juice and lemonade.
Add the sherbet with ice cream scoop.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion, carrots and celery.
Add flour and cornstarch until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and chicken broth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Stir in baking soda and cheese.
Reduce heat.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: layer of goodness
directions: Bake your favorite sheet cake.
Before cake cools completely, spread with cream cheese.
Add in layers the vanilla pudding, crushed pineapple, Cool Whip, cherries and pecans.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps well for 3 or 4 days.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix Cheddar cheese, onion and mayonnaise. Set aside.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt sugar, syrup and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add soda, salt and tartar.
Mix quickly.
Pour over popcorn and mix thoroughly.
Place in 2-inch deep pan and bake at 200° for 1 hour. Turn out on wax paper and cool.
Break apart and store in tightly closed container.

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over 1/2 package Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing.
Put layer of crumbs and layer of mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Chop onion, celery and bell pepper.
Saute with minced garlic in remaining juices.
Combine meat with mixture and spices.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cut lettuce coarsely and dice tomatoes.
Toss together in a large bowl and add slightly crushed Fritos.

title: zucchini stroganoff
directions: Place meat and onions in 10-inch skillet. Cook until beef loses pink color.
Drain.
Spread soup over beef.
Add noodles, zucchini and seasoning over beef.
Simmer, covered, until noodles are done.
Stir in sour cream and warm through.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Heat until melted. Cool.
Can be refrigerated 2 weeks.

title: oven-broiled or grilled chuck roast
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer on both sides of chuck roast and let stand 1 hour.
Salt and pepper both sides of roast.
Broil like a steak in oven at about 350°.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine all ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze to slush. Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: beef fajitas(24 servings)
directions: Heat together all ingredients, except onions and green peppers.
Grill 24 ounces sliced onion and 12 ounces sliced green peppers.
Cook until onion is transparent; set aside.

Serve with 1 (10-inch) tortilla, 2 ounces meat mixture, 1 ounce grilled onions, 1/2 ounce grilled green peppers, 1/4 ounce chopped tomato, 1/4 ounce shredded lettuce, 1/4 ounce shredded cheese and 1/4 ounce sour cream.
Wrap in the tortilla.

title: graham crackers
directions: Cream butter, sugar and honey.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together.
Add to butter mixture.
Alternate with water.
Mix well and then let it stand for 30 minutes.
Flour tabletop and roll out dough to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares, using a serrated knife or use cookie cutter for fun shapes.
Place crackers on oiled cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 3 dozen crackers.

title: pineapple dressing
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo; add eggs one at a time. Stir in pineapple and fold in bread cubes.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350° in an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole.

title: deep-dish peach pie(makes 8 servings, one 8-inch pie dish)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Remove and save 1 tablespoon sugar. In small bowl, combine remaining sugar and cornstarch. In large bowl, toss peaches and lemon juice. Add sugar mix, melted butter and extract. Turn into 8-inch round or square baking dish. Roll pastry to 9-inches. Cut slits near center. Place pastry over filling; turn under edges, seal and flute. Sprinkle (saved) 1 tablespoon of sugar and almonds on top. Bake 45 to 50 minutes or
until golden brown on top. Cool on wire rack.

title: tuna macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Drain and add tuna. Add and stir in Miracle Whip.
Finely chop the onion and stir in. Add peas.
Pour ingredients into an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Place cheese slices on top of dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Quick and easy.
Kids love it.

title: "aunt re's" corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add cornstarch, sugar, salt and melted margarine. Next, add milk and corn.
Put in buttered baking dish (7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch).
Bake 1 hour (or more if needed) at 350°.

title: ground turkey casserole
directions: Brown ground turkey and drain.
Return to pan; add garlic salt, sugar and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Cook egg noodles and drain.
Mix cream cheese, Cheddar cheese and sour cream.
Layer in 13 x 9-inch dish as follows:
egg noodles, cheese mixture and meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef tenderloin into strips.
In oil in heated skillet, brown meat 2 to 4 minutes.
Remove meat from skillet.
Add sliced mushrooms; cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove mushrooms.
Add sherry and beef broth; bring to boil.
Cook, uncovered, until liquid is reduced to 1/3.
Stir in sour cream and salt.
Stir in meat and mushrooms.
Cook slowly until heated through; do not boil.
Serve over noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, skin and remove from bones.
Place in buttered dish.
Put Swiss cheese over chicken.
In a bowl, mix soup, milk and mayonnaise.
Add frozen mixed vegetables.
Top layer is stuffing mixed with 1 stick butter.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 1 hour.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together.
Mix until blended.
Add water, vinegar, oil and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gingerbread people with storybook frosting
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Sift together remaining dry ingredients.
Mix together and chill overnight.
Roll out on floured board, making them 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into gingerbread people and bake on greased sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Scald 2 cups milk; pour over soft bread crumbs (cool).
Add next 6 ingredients.
Pour in casserole set in pan of hot water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: crunchy chicken
directions: Layer cooked chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soups (undiluted) with mayonnaise, water chestnuts and pepper.
Layer over chicken.
Layer asparagus on top.
Sprinkle crushed crackers on top.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes and, uncovered, for 15 more minutes.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
In slow cooker, combine rest of ingredients with 1 can of water.
Add meat and onion; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for about 3 hours.

title: amish salad
directions: Wash and drain sauerkraut.
Mix sugar, salad oil, vinegar and water well.
Pour over salad and marinate overnight.
Drain before serving.

title: easy seafood crepes
directions: In skillet, saute mushrooms, crab meat and broccoli with salt and pepper in margarine or butter.
Place this mixture in center of flat tortilla.
Sprinkle cheese on top and roll.
Continue until all tortillas have been filled.
Place in oblong pan. Spread soup (sour cream may be added to soup for a creamier texture) over all tortillas and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea salad(good for picnics)
directions: Assemble ingredients and layer in a large pan.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Reheat and add Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, oregano powder and Velveeta cheese.
After cheese has melted, spoon and pat on pumpernickel bread (will take 2 packs of bread).
Bake at 325° for about 5 minutes until cheese is melted.
Great for get-togethers!

title: fudge nudgies
directions: In a medium size saucepan, combine first 5 ingredients over medium to low heat.
Stir constantly, until everything is melted and blended well together.
Set this mixture aside.

title: sherry cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with crisp crackers. Makes one cup dip.

title: charcoal quail and marinade
directions: Make desired quantity proportioned as listed.
Wrap quail in bacon and grill slowly, applying the sauce continuously.

title: red pepper mayonnaise
directions: Blend on puree in blender all ingredients until smooth.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with zucchini fritters.

title: chimichaungalubbock, texas
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add taco sauce and simmer.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Mix, chill, eat and eat more!

title: mock crab imperial
directions: Put first 5 ingredients in pan.
Cook until done; drain and set aside.
Remove bay leaves.
Soften cream cheese; blend in mayonnaise, dry mustard, Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder, Old Bay seasoning and green pepper.
Carefully season with salt and pepper.
Fold in fish and put in a casserole.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon Parmesan cheese on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: snickers cake
directions: Prepare cake; pour 1/2 batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels with margarine and milk in saucepan over low heat.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Spoon remaining batter over caramel layer.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes, then at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook onion in hot margarine or butter until tender but not brown.
Add corn, broccoli, carrot and water. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes, or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, cheeses and pepper.
Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Makes 4 side dish servings.

title: quick beer bread
directions: Mix and bake in greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 375°.
Top with butter.
Cool in pan 1 hour before taking out.

title: white christmas cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and eggs. Then add brown sugar, salt, pet milk, soda, flavoring, then mix with dry ingredients of flour, nutmeg and cream of tartar.
Use more nutmeg if using more flour. Use cookie cutters for shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10-12 minutes. Cool on rack.
Frost when cool.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Combine onion, salt and cottage cheese.
Beat well with mixer. Chill several hours.
Stir in 1 tablespoon finely chopped pimiento or parsley.
Serve with celery or carrot strips.

title: marshmallow squares
directions: Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
Heat marshmallows in margarine until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Add cereal by cupfuls and stir until cereal is evenly coated.
Press into 9 x 9-inch pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in the rest; blend well.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Makes 1 (10-inch) tube pan or 2 loaves of bread.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a large paper bag.
In a 4-cup microwave-safe measure, mix rest of ingredients, except soda. Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir in the soda.
Pour mixture over corn in sack.
Microwave on High for 90 seconds.
Shake. Microwave another 90 seconds; shake.
Microwave for 40 seconds; shake.
Tear sack open; stir until cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour mixture into meat, brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: play dough
directions: Put in saucepan and cook 2 minutes.
Stir.
Knead and store in an airtight container.
